quote_original: The tendency of old age to the body, say the physiologists, is to form bone. It is as rare as it is pleasant to meet with an old man whose opinions are not ossified.
author: Bob Wells

quote_original: Old age adds to the respect due to virtue, but it takes nothing from the contempt inspired by vice it whitens only the hair.
author: Ira Gershwin

quote_original: As men get older, the toys get more expensive.
author: Marvin Davis

quote_original: I find that a man is as old as his work. If his work keeps him from moving forward, he will look forward with the work.
author: William Ernest Hocking

quote_original: Reading, after a certain age, diverts the mind too much from its creative pursuits. Any man who reads too much and uses his own brain too little falls into lazy habits of thinking.
author: Albert Einstein

quote_original: Confusion of goals and perfection of means seems, in my opinion, to characterize our age.
author: Albert Einstein

quote_original: Perfection of means and confusion of ends seem to characterize our age.
author: Albert Einstein

quote_original: The age of a woman doesn't mean a thing. The best tunes are played on the oldest fiddles.
author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

quote_original: Life would be infinitely happier if we could only be born at the age of eighty and gradually approach eighteen.
author: Mark Twain

quote_original: A stockbroker urged me to buy a stock that would triple its value every year. I told him, 'At my age, I don't even buy green bananas.'
author: Claude Pepper

quote_original: When marrying, ask yourself this question: Do you believe that you will be able to converse well with this person into your old age? Everything else in marriage is transitory.
author: Friedrich Nietzsche

quote_original: Probably the happiest period in life most frequently is in middle age, when the eager passions of youth are cooled, and the infirmities of age not yet begun as we see that the shadows, which are at morning and evening so large, almost entirely disappear at midday.
author: Eleanor Roosevelt

quote_original: As human beings, our greatness lies not so much in being able to remake the world - that is the myth of the atomic age - as in being able to remake ourselves.
author: Mahatma Gandhi

quote_original: A man loves the meat in his youth that he cannot endure in his age.
author: William Shakespeare

quote_original: In every country and every age, the priest had been hostile to Liberty.
author: Thomas Jefferson

quote_original: The heresy of one age becomes the orthodoxy of the next.
author: Helen Keller

quote_original: Every formula of every religion has in this age of reason, to submit to the acid test of reason and universal assent.
author: Mahatma Gandhi

quote_original: Thomas Jefferson once said, 'We should never judge a president by his age, only by his works.' And ever since he told me that, I stopped worrying.
author: Ronald Reagan

quote_original: No woman should ever be quite accurate about her age. It looks so calculating.
author: Oscar Wilde

quote_original: At twenty years of age the will reigns at thirty, the wit and at forty, the judgment.
author: Benjamin Franklin

quote_original: Information is the oxygen of the modern age. It seeps through the walls topped by barbed wire, it wafts across the electrified borders.
author: Ronald Reagan

quote_original: Old age is just a record of one's whole life.
author: Muhammad Ali

quote_original: We prefer world law in the age of self-determination to world war in the age of mass extermination.
author: John F. Kennedy

quote_original: Each age, it is found, must write its own books or rather, each generation for the next succeeding.
author: Ralph Waldo Emerson

quote_original: Education is the best provision for old age.
author: Aristotle

quote_original: The secret of staying young is to live honestly, eat slowly, and lie about your age.
author: Lucille Ball

quote_original: Sometimes I think it would be easier to avoid old age, to die young, but then you'd never complete your life, would you? You'd never wholly know you.
author: Marilyn Monroe

quote_original: I don't think of myself as a poor deprived ghetto girl who made good. I think of myself as somebody who from an early age knew I was responsible for myself, and I had to make good.
author: Oprah Winfrey

quote_original: The kids are old enough now - I just want to let them be kids. I don't want to comment on them too much. They're at an age where I just want to let them be kids.
author: Eminem

quote_original: He who is of calm and happy nature will hardly feel the pressure of age, but to him who is of an opposite disposition youth and age are equally a burden.
author: Plato

quote_original: Why should society feel responsible only for the education of children, and not for the education of all adults of every age?
author: Erich Fromm

quote_original: I've got volumes on how not to behave. I've got more information now than a guy should have at my age.
author: Charlie Sheen

quote_original: I'm at the age where food has taken the place of sex in my life. In fact, I've just had a mirror put over my kitchen table.
author: Rodney Dangerfield

quote_original: Age is something that doesn't matter, unless you are a cheese.
author: Luis Bunuel

quote_original: Books were my pass to personal freedom. I learned to read at age three, and soon discovered there was a whole world to conquer that went beyond our farm in Mississippi.
author: Oprah Winfrey

quote_original: In our age there is no such thing as 'keeping out of politics.' All issues are political issues, and politics itself is a mass of lies, evasions, folly, hatred and schizophrenia.
author: George Orwell

quote_original: I must confess, I was born at a very early age.
author: Groucho Marx

quote_original: The secret of genius is to carry the spirit of the child into old age, which mean never losing your enthusiasm.
author: Aldous Huxley

quote_original: It is utterly false and cruelly arbitrary to put all the play and learning into childhood, all the work into middle age, and all the regrets into old age.
author: Margaret Mead

quote_original: We aren't in an information age, we are in an entertainment age.
author: Tony Robbins

quote_original: To me - old age is always ten years older than I am.
author: John Burroughs

quote_original: Age is not important unless you're a cheese.
author: Helen Hayes

quote_original: No matter what age you are, or what your circumstances might be, you are special, and you still have something unique to offer. Your life, because of who you are, has meaning.
author: Barbara de Angelis

quote_original: A woman has the age she deserves.
author: Coco Chanel

quote_original: The older I grow the more I distrust the familiar doctrine that age brings wisdom.
author: H. L. Mencken

quote_original: Youngsters of the age of two and three are endowed with extraordinary strength. They can lift a dog twice their own weight and dump him into the bathtub.
author: Erma Bombeck

quote_original: He who has not the spirit of this age, has all the misery of it.
author: Voltaire

quote_original: Instead of being presented with stereotypes by age, sex, color, class, or religion, children must have the opportunity to learn that within each range, some people are loathsome and some are delightful.
author: Margaret Mead

quote_original: I think being able to age gracefully is a very important talent. It is too late for me.
author: Clint Eastwood

quote_original: Error is acceptable as long as we are young but one must not drag it along into old age.
author: Johann Wolfgang von Goethe

quote_original: Age wrinkles the body. Quitting wrinkles the soul.
author: Douglas MacArthur

quote_original: I don't need you to remind me of my age. I have a bladder to do that for me.
author: Stephen Fry

quote_original: Talk is by far the most accessible of pleasures. It costs nothing in money, it is all profit, it completes our education, founds and fosters our friendships, and can be enjoyed at any age and in almost any state of health.
author: Robert Louis Stevenson

quote_original: Men of age object too much, consult too long, adventure too little, repent too soon, and seldom drive business home to the full period, but content themselves with a mediocrity of success.
author: Dale Carnegie

quote_original: Better pass boldly into that other world, in the full glory of some passion, than fade and wither dismally with age.
author: James Joyce

quote_original: Age merely shows what children we remain.
author: Johann Wolfgang von Goethe

quote_original: Each moment of a happy lover's hour is worth an age of dull and common life.
author: Aphra Behn

quote_original: The credit of advancing science has always been due to individuals and never to the age.
author: Johann Wolfgang von Goethe

quote_original: Dressing up is a bore. At a certain age, you decorate yourself to attract the opposite sex, and at a certain age, I did that. But I'm past that age.
author: Katharine Hepburn

quote_original: I was born at the age of twelve on an MGM lot.
author: Judy Garland

quote_original: A woman telling her true age is like a buyer confiding his final price to an Armenian rug dealer.
author: Mignon McLaughlin

quote_original: How young can you die of old age?
author: Steven Wright

quote_original: Legend: A lie that has attained the dignity of age.
author: H. L. Mencken

quote_original: Age does not protect you from love. But love, to some extent, protects you from age.
author: Jeanne Moreau

quote_original: Every great architect is - necessarily - a great poet. He must be a great original interpreter of his time, his day, his age.
author: Frank Lloyd Wright

quote_original: At the age of six I wanted to be a cook. At seven I wanted to be Napoleon. And my ambition has been growing steadily ever since.
author: Salvador Dali

quote_original: Middle age is when you're sitting at home on a Saturday night and the telephone rings and you hope it isn't for you.
author: Ogden Nash

quote_original: If youth knew if age could.
author: Sigmund Freud

quote_original: I think the biggest disease the world suffers from in this day and age is the disease of people feeling unloved. I know that I can give love for a minute, for half an hour, for a day, for a month, but I can give. I am very happy to do that, I want to do that.
author: Princess Diana

quote_original: The charm of history and its enigmatic lesson consist in the fact that, from age to age, nothing changes and yet everything is completely different.
author: Aldous Huxley

quote_original: Men are like wine - some turn to vinegar, but the best improve with age.
author: Pope John XXIII

quote_original: I created Punk for this day and age. Do you see Britney walking around wearing ties and singing punk? Hell no. That's what I do. I'm like a Sid Vicious for a new generation.
author: Avril Lavigne

quote_original: We are all geniuses up to the age of ten.
author: Aldous Huxley

quote_original: It is well for the world that in most of us, by the age of thirty, the character has set like plaster, and will never soften again.
author: William James

quote_original: Every age has its own poetry in every age the circumstances of history choose a nation, a race, a class to take up the torch by creating situations that can be expressed or transcended only through poetry.
author: Jean-Paul Sartre

quote_original: Old age is not a matter for sorrow. It is matter for thanks if we have left our work done behind us.
author: Thomas Carlyle

quote_original: I suppose when they reach a certain age some men are afraid to grow up. It seems the older the men get, the younger their new wives get.
author: Elizabeth Taylor

quote_original: Sex at age 90 is like trying to shoot pool with a rope.
author: George Burns

quote_original: Publishing is in a kind of Jurassic age.
author: Paulo Coelho

quote_original: Age is just a number. It's totally irrelevant unless, of course, you happen to be a bottle of wine.
author: Joan Collins

quote_original: Whatever you may look like, marry a man your own age - as your beauty fades, so will his eyesight.
author: Phyllis Diller

quote_original: Youth has no age.
author: Pablo Picasso

quote_original: Youth is a blunder Manhood a struggle, Old Age a regret.
author: Benjamin Disraeli

quote_original: To teach how to live without certainty and yet without being paralysed by hesitation is perhaps the chief thing that philosophy, in our age, can do for those who study it.
author: Bertrand Russell

quote_original: It is possible that mankind is on the threshold of a golden age but, if so, it will be necessary first to slay the dragon that guards the door, and this dragon is religion.
author: Bertrand Russell

quote_original: Nobody expects to trust his body overmuch after the age of fifty.
author: Alexander Hamilton

quote_original: Old age realizes the dreams of youth: look at Dean Swift in his youth he built an asylum for the insane, in his old age he was himself an inmate.
author: Soren Kierkegaard

quote_original: In youth we learn in age we understand.
author: Marie von Ebner-Eschenbach

quote_original: Believe me, that was a happy age, before the days of architects, before the days of builders.
author: Lucius Annaeus Seneca

quote_original: I have the problems of, I must confess, old age.
author: Billy Graham

quote_original: Not just in commerce but in the world of ideas too our age is putting on a veritable clearance sale. Everything can be had so dirt cheap that one begins to wonder whether in the end anyone will want to make a bid.
author: Soren Kierkegaard

quote_original: Bad news isn't wine. It doesn't improve with age.
author: Colin Powell

quote_original: It were a real increase of human happiness, could all young men from the age of nineteen be covered under barrels, or rendered otherwise invisible and there left to follow their lawful studies and callings, till they emerged, sadder and wiser, at the age of twenty-five.
author: Thomas Carlyle

quote_original: People who refuse to rest honorably on their laurels when they reach retirement age seem very admirable to me.
author: Helen Hayes

quote_original: Not to expose your true feelings to an adult seems to be instinctive from the age of seven or eight onwards.
author: George Orwell

quote_original: The heart never grows better by age I fear rather worse, always harder. A young liar will be an old one, and a young knave will only be a greater knave as he grows older.
author: Lord Chesterfield

quote_original: For age is opportunity no less Than youth itself, though in another dress, And as the evening twilight fades away The sky is filled with stars, invisible by day.
author: Henry Wadsworth Longfellow

quote_original: Age is a case of mind over matter. If you don't mind, it don't matter.
author: Satchel Paige

quote_original: Have regular hours for work and play make each day both useful and pleasant, and prove that you understand the worth of time by employing it well. Then youth will be delightful, old age will bring few regrets, and life will become a beautiful success.
author: Louisa May Alcott

quote_original: Admiration of the proletariat, like that of dams, power stations, and aeroplanes, is part of the ideology of the machine age.
author: Bertrand Russell

quote_original: But the age of chivalry is gone. That of sophisters, economists, and calculators has succeeded and the glory of Europe is extinguished forever.
author: Edmund Burke

quote_original: Childhood: the period of human life intermediate between the idiocy of infancy and the folly of youth - two removes from the sin of manhood and three from the remorse of age.
author: Ambrose Bierce

quote_original: Experience is a revelation in the light of which we renounce our errors of youth for those of age.
author: Ambrose Bierce

quote_original: The ruling ideas of each age have ever been the ideas of its ruling class.
author: Karl Marx

quote_original: In the information age, you don't teach philosophy as they did after feudalism. You perform it. If Aristotle were alive today he'd have a talk show.
author: Timothy Leary

quote_original: Once I planned to write a book of poems entirely about the things in my pocket. But I found it would be too long and the age of the great epics is past.
author: Gilbert K. Chesterton

quote_original: The harvest of old age is the recollection and abundance of blessing previously secured.
author: Marcus Tullius Cicero

quote_original: It is the spirit of the age to believe that any fact, no matter how suspect, is superior to any imaginative exercise, no matter how true.
author: Gore Vidal

quote_original: The arrogance of age must submit to be taught by youth.
author: Edmund Burke

quote_original: The biggest disease this day and age is that of people feeling unloved.
author: Princess Diana

quote_original: Old age: the crown of life, our play's last act.
author: Marcus Tullius Cicero

quote_original: I think women should start to embrace their age. What's the alternative to getting older? You die. I can't change the day I was born. But I can take care of my skin, my body, my mind, and try to live my life and be happy.
author: Olivia Munn

quote_original: Age is getting to know all the ways the world turns, so that if you cannot turn the world the way you want, you can at least get out of the way so you won't get run over.
author: Miriam Makeba

quote_original: Few women, I fear, have had such reason as I have to think the long sad years of youth were worth living for the sake of middle age.
author: Dwight D. Eisenhower

quote_original: One crowded hour of glorious life is worth an age without a name.
author: Walter Scott

quote_original: Wives are young men's mistresses, companions for middle age, and old men's nurses.
author: Francis Bacon

quote_original: Wisdom doesn't necessarily come with age. Sometimes age just shows up all by itself.
author: Tom Wilson

quote_original: It is a blessed thing that in every age some one has had the individuality enough and courage enough to stand by his own convictions.
author: Robert Green Ingersoll

quote_original: And in my own life, in my own small way, I've tried to give back to this country that has given me so much. That's why I left a job at a law firm for a career in public service, working to empower young people to volunteer in their communities. Because I believe that each of us - no matter what our age or background or walk of life - each of us has something to contribute to the life of this nation.
author: Michelle Obama

quote_original: No lying knight or lying priest ever prospered in any age, but especially not in the dark ones. Men prospered then only in following an openly declared purpose, and preaching candidly beloved and trusted creeds.
author: John Ruskin

quote_original: A man does not die of love or his liver or even of old age he dies of being a man.
author: Miguel de Unamuno

quote_original: It is with an old love as it is with old age a man lives to all the miseries, but is dead to all the pleasures.
author: Francois de La Rochefoucauld

quote_original: I cried on my 18th birthday. I thought 17 was such a nice age. You're young enough to get away with things, but you're old enough, too.
author: Liv Tyler

quote_original: We live in an age when to be young and to be indifferent can be no longer synonymous. We must prepare for the coming hour. The claims of the Future are represented by suffering millions and the Youth of a Nation are the trustees of Posterity.
author: Benjamin Disraeli

quote_original: Age shouldn't affect you. It's just like the size of your shoes - they don't determine how you live your life! You're either marvellous or you're boring, regardless of your age.
author: Steven Morrissey

quote_original: Rashness belongs to youth prudence to old age.
author: Marcus Tullius Cicero

quote_original: Many believe - and I believe - that I have been designated for this work by God. In spite of my old age, I do not want to give it up I work out of love for God and I put all my hope in Him.
author: Michelangelo

quote_original: Old age is a tyrant, who forbids, under pain of death, the pleasures of youth.
author: Francois de La Rochefoucauld

quote_original: The defects of the mind, like those of the face, grow worse with age.
author: Francois de La Rochefoucauld

quote_original: The enemy of society is middle class and the enemy of life is middle age.
author: Orson Welles

quote_original: Some say that the age of chivalry is past, that the spirit of romance is dead. The age of chivalry is never past, so long as there is a wrong left unredressed on earth.
author: Charles Kingsley

quote_original: Man has no Body distinct from his Soul for that called Body is a portion of Soul discerned by the five Senses, the chief inlets of Soul in this age.
author: William Blake

quote_original: Do you remember when you were 10 or 11 years old and you really thought your folks were the best? They were completely omniscient and you took their word for everything. And then you got older and you went through this hideous age when suddenly they were the devil, they were bullies, and they didn't know anything.
author: Chuck Palahniuk

quote_original: This is the patent age of new inventions for killing bodies, and for saving souls. All propagated with the best intentions.
author: Lord Byron

quote_original: The mind that is wise mourns less for what age takes away than what it leaves behind.
author: William Wordsworth

quote_original: The age of chivalry is past. Bores have succeeded to dragons.
author: Charles Dickens

quote_original: Anything you cannot relinquish when it has outlived its usefulness possesses you, and in this materialistic age a great many of us are possessed by our possessions.
author: Peace Pilgrim

quote_original: Like many women my age, I am 28 years old.
author: Mary Schmich

quote_original: Life, an age to the miserable, and a moment to the happy.
author: Francis Bacon

quote_original: We are always the same age inside.
author: Gertrude Stein

quote_original: I am, as I've said, merely competent. But in an age of incompetence, that makes me extraordinary.
author: Billy Joel

quote_original: Swing voters are more appropriately known as the 'idiot voters' because they have no set of philosophical principles. By the age of fourteen, you're either a Conservative or a Liberal if you have an IQ above a toaster.
author: Ann Coulter

quote_original: If you live to be one hundred, you've got it made. Very few people die past that age.
author: George Burns

quote_original: Old age is far more than white hair, wrinkles, the feeling that it is too late and the game finished, that the stage belongs to the rising generations. The true evil is not the weakening of the body, but the indifference of the soul.
author: Andre Maurois

quote_original: Old age has its pleasures, which, though different, are not less than the pleasures of youth.
author: W. Somerset Maugham

quote_original: Old age is when the liver spots show through your gloves.
author: Phyllis Diller

quote_original: There is no absurdity so palpable but that it may be firmly planted in the human head if you only begin to inculcate it before the age of five, by constantly repeating it with an air of great solemnity.
author: Arthur Schopenhauer

quote_original: Those who improve with age embrace the power of personal growth and personal achievement and begin to replace youth with wisdom, innocence with understanding, and lack of purpose with self-actualization.
author: Bo Bennett

quote_original: Nearly all the powerful people of this age are unbelievers, the best of them in doubt and misery, the most in plodding hesitation, doing as well as they can, what practical work lies at hand.
author: John Ruskin

quote_original: What is an adult? A child blown up by age.
author: Simone de Beauvoir

quote_original: Intelligent life on a planet comes of age when it first works out the reason for its own existence.
author: Richard Dawkins

quote_original: I am of a healthy long lived race, and our minds improve with age.
author: William Butler Yeats

quote_original: The wisdom of age: don't stop walking.
author: Mason Cooley

quote_original: As the age of television progresses the Reagans will be the rule, not the exception. To be perfect for television is all a President has to be these days.
author: Gore Vidal

quote_original: Before anything else, we need a new age of Enlightenment. Our present political systems must relinquish their claims on truth, justice and freedom and have to replace them with the search for truth, justice, freedom and reason.
author: Friedrich Durrenmatt

quote_original: Age is strictly a case of mind over matter. If you don't mind, it doesn't matter.
author: Jack Benny

quote_original: 'Age' is the acceptance of a term of years. But maturity is the glory of years.
author: Martha Graham

quote_original: I think we ought to raise the age at which juveniles can have a gun.
author: George W. Bush

quote_original: In this age, which believes that there is a short cut to everything, the greatest lesson to be learned is that the most difficult way is, in the long run, the easiest.
author: Henry Miller

quote_original: A man is a fool if he drinks before he reaches the age of 50, and a fool if he doesn't afterward.
author: Frank Lloyd Wright

quote_original: There are few things that we so unwillingly give up, even in advanced age, as the supposition that we still have the power of ingratiating ourselves with the fair sex.
author: Samuel Johnson

quote_original: Age imprints more wrinkles in the mind than it does on the face.
author: Michel de Montaigne

quote_original: I was confirmed at my prep school at the age of 13.
author: Richard Dawkins

quote_original: Love has no age, no limit and no death.
author: John Galsworthy

quote_original: What makes old age hard to bear is not the failing of one's faculties, mental and physical, but the burden of one's memories.
author: W. Somerset Maugham

quote_original: I have always paid income tax. I object only when it reaches a stage when I am threatened with having nothing left for my old age - which is due to start next Tuesday or Wednesday.
author: Noel Coward

quote_original: In my youth I stressed freedom, and in my old age I stress order. I have made the great discovery that liberty is a product of order.
author: Will Durant

quote_original: And I'm afraid, in this day and age, trust, which I count so, you know, I love loyalty. I love trust.
author: Elton John

quote_original: My dad encouraged us to fail. Growing up, he would ask us what we failed at that week. If we didn't have something, he would be disappointed. It changed my mindset at an early age that failure is not the outcome, failure is not trying. Don't be afraid to fail.
author: Sara Blakely

quote_original: What is the worst of woes that wait on age? What stamps the wrinkle deeper on the brow? To view each loved one blotted from life's page, And be alone on earth, as I am now.
author: Lord Byron

quote_original: Age is a matter of feeling, not of years.
author: Washington Irving

quote_original: A tart temper never mellows with age, and a sharp tongue is the only edged tool that grows keener with constant use.
author: Washington Irving

quote_original: Canada has a passive-aggressive culture, with a lot of sarcasm and righteousness. That went with my weird messianic complex. The ego is a fascinating monster. I was taught from a young age that I had to serve, so that turned into me thinking I had to save the planet.
author: Alanis Morissette

quote_original: Discrimination due to age is one of the great tragedies of modern life. The desire to work and be useful is what makes life worth living, and to be told your efforts are not needed because you are the wrong age is a crime.
author: Johnny Ball

quote_original: An artist must be a reactionary. He has to stand out against the tenor of the age and not go flopping along.
author: Andre Maurois

quote_original: What turns me on about the digital age, what excited me personally, is that you have closed the gap between dreaming and doing. You see, it used to be that if you wanted to make a record of a song, you needed a studio and a producer. Now, you need a laptop.
author: Bono

quote_original: I have always felt that a woman has the right to treat the subject of her age with ambiguity until, perhaps, she passes into the realm of over ninety. Then it is better she be candid with herself and with the world.
author: Carl Sandburg

quote_original: Nice to be here? At my age it's nice to be anywhere.
author: George Burns

quote_original: Though the Jazz Age continued it became less and less an affair of youth. The sequel was like a children's party taken over by the elders.
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald

quote_original: Each age has deemed the new-born year the fittest time for festal cheer.
author: Walter Scott

quote_original: Our age knows nothing but reaction, and leaps from one extreme to another.
author: Reinhold Niebuhr

quote_original: The philosophies of one age have become the absurdities of the next, and the foolishness of yesterday has become the wisdom of tomorrow.
author: William Osler

quote_original: I saw no African people in the printed and illustrated Sunday school lessons. I began to suspect at this early age that someone had distorted the image of my people. My long search for the true history of African people the world over began.
author: John Henrik Clarke

quote_original: In order to fix Social Security, we must restructure it so that we continue to provide for our Nation's seniors that are approaching retirement age, but allow for younger taxpayers to invest a portion of their Social Security taxes in private accounts.
author: Herman Cain

quote_original: No lie ever reaches old age.
author: Sophocles

quote_original: I wanted to be a teacher. I love children, so I wanted to deal with children. Then I wanted to be a veterinarian. But by the age of ten or eleven, when I opened my mouth and said, 'Oh, God, what's this?' I kind of knew teaching and being a veterinarian were gonna have to wait.
author: Whitney Houston

quote_original: This is the curse of our age, even the strangest aberrations are no cure for boredom.
author: Stendhal

quote_original: If repression has indeed been the fundamental link between power, knowledge, and sexuality since the classical age, it stands to reason that we will not be able to free ourselves from it except at a considerable cost.
author: Michel Foucault

quote_original: But an old age serene and bright, and lovely as a Lapland night, shall lead thee to thy grave.
author: William Wordsworth

quote_original: Litigation takes the place of sex at middle age.
author: Gore Vidal

quote_original: The face you have at age 25 is the face God gave you, but the face you have after 50 is the face you earned.
author: Cindy Crawford

quote_original: The hallmark of our age is the tension between aspirations and sluggish institutions.
author: John W. Gardner

quote_original: It seems as if an age of genius must be succeeded by an age of endeavour riot and extravagance by cleanliness and hard work.
author: Virginia Woolf

quote_original: Old age is ready to undertake tasks that youth shirked because they would take too long.
author: W. Somerset Maugham

quote_original: A woman tells her doctor, 'I've got a bad back.' The doctor says, 'It's old age.' The woman says, 'I want a second opinion.' The doctor says: 'Okay - you're ugly as well.'
author: Tommy Cooper

quote_original: I'm 36 and if I met a woman of my own age and married her, I'd also be marrying her former life, her past. It might be OK for some people - I don't want to judge it or anything - but it's not for me. It would destroy my creativity.
author: Henry Rollins

quote_original: I believe we should encourage children to sing and play instruments from an early age.
author: Mick Jagger

quote_original: You should not consider a man's age but his acts.
author: Sophocles

quote_original: At my age flowers scare me.
author: George Burns

quote_original: I would go out with women my age, but there are no women my age.
author: George Burns

quote_original: It is not well to make great changes in old age.
author: Charles Spurgeon

quote_original: Setting a good example for your children takes all the fun out of middle age.
author: William Feather

quote_original: You are 27 or 28 right? It is very tough to live at that age. When nothing is sure. I have sympathy with you.
author: Haruki Murakami

quote_original: The stars shall fade away, the sun himself Grow dim with age, and nature sink in years, But thou shalt flourish in immortal youth, Unhurt amidst the wars of elements, The wrecks of matter, and the crush of worlds.
author: Joseph Addison

quote_original: Young men soon give, and soon forget, affronts old age is slow in both.
author: Joseph Addison

quote_original: By all but the pathologically romantic, it is now recognized that this is not the age of the small man.
author: John Kenneth Galbraith

quote_original: It is not the young people that degenerate they are not spoiled till those of mature age are already sunk into corruption.
author: Charles de Montesquieu

quote_original: To be happy, we must be true to nature and carry our age along with us.
author: William Hazlitt

quote_original: Youth cannot know how age thinks and feels. But old men are guilty if they forget what it was to be young.
author: J. K. Rowling

quote_original: It is the malady of our age that the young are so busy teaching us that they have no time left to learn.
author: Eric Hoffer

quote_original: I'm at peace with myself and where I am. In the past, I was always looking to see how everybody else was doing. I wasn't competitive, I was comparative. I just wanted to be where everybody else was. Now I've gotten to an age when I am not comparing anymore.
author: Courteney Cox

quote_original: We of Africa protest that, in this day and age, we should continue to be treated as lesser human beings than other races.
author: Robert Mugabe

quote_original: Marriage is not about age it's about finding the right person.
author: Sophia Bush

quote_original: We have entered an age in which education is not just a luxury permitting some men an advantage over others. It has become a necessity without which a person is defenseless in this complex, industrialized society. We have truly entered the century of the educated man.
author: Lyndon B. Johnson

quote_original: Old age is the verdict of life.
author: Amelia Barr

quote_original: The passions grafted on wounded pride are the most inveterate they are green and vigorous in old age.
author: George Santayana

quote_original: Every age can be enchanting, provided you live within it.
author: Brigitte Bardot

quote_original: It is unthinkable for a Frenchman to arrive at middle age without having syphilis and the Cross of the Legion of Honor.
author: Andre Gide

quote_original: It is folly for an eminent man to think of escaping censure, and a weakness to be affected with it. All the illustrious persons of antiquity, and indeed of every age in the world, have passed through this fiery persecution.
author: Joseph Addison

quote_original: There must be a day or two in a man's life when he is the precise age for something important.
author: Franklin P. Adams

quote_original: It is old age, rather than death, that is to be contrasted with life. Old age is life's parody, whereas death transforms life into a destiny: in a way it preserves it by giving it the absolute dimension. Death does away with time.
author: Simone de Beauvoir

quote_original: I don't care about age very much.
author: Chinua Achebe

quote_original: Old age and the passage of time teach all things.
author: Sophocles

quote_original: I think age is a very high price to pay for maturity.
author: Tom Stoppard

quote_original: I had used eclectic therapy and behavior therapy on myself at the age of 19 to get over my fear of public speaking and of approaching young women in public.
author: Albert Ellis

quote_original: Children rarely want to know who their parents were before they were parents, and when age finally stirs their curiosity, there is no parent left to tell them.
author: Russell Baker

quote_original: Middle age occurs when you are too young to take up golf and too old to rush up to the net.
author: Franklin P. Adams

quote_original: Old age: I fall asleep during the funerals of my friends.
author: Mason Cooley

quote_original: Staid middle age loves the hurricane passions of opera.
author: Mason Cooley

quote_original: Middle age went by while I was mourning for my lost youth.
author: Mason Cooley

quote_original: In passing, we should note this curious mark of our own age: the only absolute allowed is the absolute insistence that there is no absolute.
author: Francis Schaeffer

quote_original: It's not catastrophes, murders, deaths, diseases, that age and kill us it's the way people look and laugh, and run up the steps of omnibuses.
author: Virginia Woolf

quote_original: Not even old age knows how to love death.
author: Sophocles

quote_original: It's really amazing that in the age of unbelief, as a smart man called it, there isn't even more fraud. After all, with no God, there's no one to ever call you to account, and no accounting at all if you can get away with it.
author: Ben Stein

quote_original: I think that a man should not live beyond the age when he begins to deteriorate, when the flame that lighted the brightest moment of his life has weakened.
author: Fidel Castro

quote_original: Temper never mellows with age, and a sharp tongue is the only edged tool that grows keener with constant use.
author: Washington Irving

quote_original: It is not by the gray of the hair that one knows the age of the heart.
author: Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton

quote_original: I think the sport of wrestling, which I became involved with at the age of 14... I competed until I was 34, kind of old for a contact sport. I coached the sport until I was 47. I think the discipline of wrestling has given me the discipline I have to write.
author: John Irving

quote_original: Another belief of mine that everyone else my age is an adult, whereas I am merely in disguise.
author: Margaret Atwood

quote_original: Age carries all things away, even the mind.
author: Virgil

quote_original: Age steals away all things, even the mind.
author: Virgil

quote_original: In fact, my courage and my bravery at a young age was the thing I was bullied for, a kind of 'Who do you think you are?'
author: Lady Gaga

quote_original: A bad manner spoils everything, even reason and justice a good one supplies everything, gilds a No, sweetens a truth, and adds a touch of beauty to old age itself.
author: Baltasar Gracian

quote_original: As technology advances, it reverses the characteristics of every situation again and again. The age of automation is going to be the age of 'do it yourself.'
author: Marshall McLuhan

quote_original: The excess of our youth are checks written against our age and they are payable with interest thirty years later.
author: Charles Caleb Colton

quote_original: At the age when Bengali youth almost inevitably writes poetry, I was listening to European classical music.
author: Satyajit Ray

quote_original: I smoke ten to fifteen cigars a day. At my age I have to hold on to something.
author: George Burns

quote_original: I'm at the age now where just putting my cigar in its holder is a thrill.
author: George Burns

quote_original: Age becomes reality when you hear someone refer to that attractive young woman standing next to the woman in the green dress, and you find that you're the one in the green dress.
author: Lois Wyse

quote_original: Our scientific age demands that we provide definitions, measurements, and statistics in order to be taken seriously. Yet most of the important things in life cannot be precisely defined or measured. Can we define or measure love, beauty, friendship, or decency, for example?
author: Dennis Prager

quote_original: The nearer people approach old age the closer they return to a semblance of childhood, until the time comes for them to depart this life, again like children, neither tired of living nor aware of death.
author: Desiderius Erasmus

quote_original: Old age is a special problem for me because I've never been able to shed the mental image I have of myself - a lad of about 19.
author: E. B. White

quote_original: People until I was 60 would always say they thought I looked younger, which I think, without flattering myself, I did, but I think I certainly have, as George Orwell says people do after a certain age, the face they deserve.
author: Christopher Hitchens

quote_original: The one thing that unites all human beings, regardless of age, gender, religion or ethnic background, is that we all believe we are above-average drivers.
author: Dave Barry

quote_original: Why do people talk of the horrors of old age? It's great. I feel like a fine old car with the parts gradually wearing out, but I'm not complaining,... Those who find growing old terrible are people who haven't done what they wanted with their lives.
author: Martha Gellhorn

quote_original: As winter strips the leaves from around us, so that we may see the distant regions they formerly concealed, so old age takes away our enjoyments only to enlarge the prospect of the coming eternity.
author: Jean Paul

quote_original: God employs several translators some pieces are translated by age, some by sickness, some by war, some by justice.
author: John Donne

quote_original: No man was ever so completely skilled in the conduct of life, as not to receive new information from age and experience.
author: Jonathan Swift

quote_original: Interest is the spur of the people, but glory that of great souls. Invention is the talent of youth, and judgment of age.
author: Jonathan Swift

quote_original: Invention is the talent of youth, as judgment is of age.
author: Jonathan Swift

quote_original: I'm very pleased to be here. Let's face it, at my age I'm very pleased to be anywhere.
author: George Burns

quote_original: I must be more sensible and realize that at my age, illusions are hardly permitted and they will always destroy me.
author: Paul Cezanne

quote_original: My age and health will never allow me to realize the dream of art I've been pursuing all my life.
author: Paul Cezanne

quote_original: My husband gave me a necklace. It's fake. I requested fake. Maybe I'm paranoid, but in this day and age, I don't want something around my neck that's worth more than my head.
author: Rita Rudner

quote_original: From as long as, literally as far back as I can remember I've liked puns, word jokes, I can literally recall looking at a comic at the age of six or seven and I remember what I enjoyed and what it was precisely and how the joke worked.
author: Tom Stoppard

quote_original: The terror of the atom age is not the violence of the new power but the speed of man's adjustment to it, the speed of his acceptance.
author: E. B. White

quote_original: I was born in ancient times, at the end of the world, in a patriarchal Catholic and conservative family. No wonder that by age five I was a raging feminist - although the term had not reached Chile yet, so nobody knew what the heck was wrong with me.
author: Isabel Allende

quote_original: The information encoded in your DNA determines your unique biological characteristics, such as sex, eye color, age and Social Security number.
author: Dave Barry

quote_original: O love, if I regret the age when one savors you, it is not for the hour of pleasure, but for the one that follows it.
author: Jean-Jacques Rousseau

quote_original: In the television age, the key distinction is between the candidate who can speak poetry and the one who can only speak prose.
author: Richard M. Nixon

quote_original: Age does not matter if the matter does not age.
author: Jean Paul

quote_original: I'm well past the age where I'm acceptable. You get to a certain age and you are forbidden access. You're not going to get the kind of coverage that you would like in music magazines, you're not going to get played on radio and you're not going to get played on television. I have to survive on word of mouth.
author: David Bowie

quote_original: Ours is essentially a tragic age, so we refuse to take it tragically.
author: David Herbert Lawrence

quote_original: Ours is an excessively conscious age. We know so much, we feel so little.
author: David Herbert Lawrence

quote_original: Everybody past a certain age, regardless of how they look on the outside, pretty much constantly dreams of being able to escape from their lives.
author: Doug Coupland

quote_original: One keeps forgetting old age up to the very brink of the grave.
author: Sidonie Gabrielle Colette

quote_original: In the age of the individual's liquidation, the question of individuality must be raised anew.
author: Theodor Adorno

quote_original: I ask you to pray for me, for once age has overtaken us, we find consolation only in religion.
author: Paul Cezanne

quote_original: Today more than ever we need creative minds to address the issues of the age. And one of the most urgent is this: How can humanity know so much, achieve so much, and still fail so many people so badly?
author: King Abdullah II

quote_original: Women lie about their age men lie about their income.
author: William Feather

quote_original: A major advantage of age is learning to accept people without passing judgment.
author: Liz Carpenter

quote_original: The people who live in a golden age usually go around complaining how yellow everything looks.
author: Randall Jarrell

quote_original: There was no respect for youth when I was young, and now that I am old, there is no respect for age, I missed it coming and going.
author: J. B. Priestley

quote_original: Everyone knows that by far the happiest and universally enjoyable age of man is the first. What is there about babies which makes us hug and kiss and fondle them, so that even an enemy would give them help at that age?
author: Desiderius Erasmus

quote_original: Well, I'm in my 60s now. I finally look it, I think. People until I was 60 would always say they thought I looked younger, which I think, without flattering myself, I did, but I think I certainly have, as George Orwell says people do after a certain age, the face they deserve.
author: Christopher Hitchens

quote_original: 'Bombing Afghanistan back into the Stone Age' was quite a favourite headline for some wobbly liberals. The slogan does all the work. But an instant's thought shows that Afghanistan is being, if anything, bombed out of the Stone Age.
author: Christopher Hitchens

quote_original: Oh, if I had been loved at the age of seventeen, what an idiot I would be today. Happiness is like smallpox: if you catch it too soon, it can completely ruin your constitution.
author: Gustave Flaubert

quote_original: English people don't have very good diction. In France you have to pronounce very particularly and clearly, and learning French at an early age helped me enormously.
author: Vivien Leigh

quote_original: Children also have artistic ability, and there is wisdom in there having it! The more helpless they are, the more instructive are the examples they furnish us and they must be preserved free of corruption from an early age.
author: Paul Klee

quote_original: Of course, the ideal scenario for parenting is obviously two parents of a mature age.
author: Jennifer Aniston

quote_original: You know what makes me feel old? When I see girls who are 20-something, or the new crop of actresses, and think, Aren't we kind of the same age?
author: Jennifer Aniston

quote_original: I think love can happen at any age... it has no age.
author: Shahrukh Khan

quote_original: Elizabeth Peyton, the artist known for tiny, dazzling portraits of radiant youth, is now painting tiny, dazzling portraits of radiant middle age.
author: Jerry Saltz

quote_original: I'm inspired by people who keep on rolling, no matter their age.
author: Jimmy Buffett

quote_original: By Time and Age full many things are taught.
author: Aeschylus

quote_original: I was taught from a young age that I had to serve, so that turned into me thinking I had to save the planet.
author: Alanis Morissette

quote_original: If you've got to my age, you've probably had your heart broken many times. So it's not that difficult to unpack a bit of grief from some little corner of your heart and cry over it.
author: Emma Thompson

quote_original: My mother enjoyed old age, and because of her I've begun to enjoy parts of it too. So far I've had it good and am crumbling nicely.
author: Lionel Blue

quote_original: We're saying no changes for Medicare for people above the age of 55. And in order to keep the promise to current seniors who've already retired and organized their lives around this program, you have to reform it for the next generation.
author: Paul Ryan

quote_original: It's sad, actually, because my anxiety keeps me from enjoying things as much as I should at this age.
author: Amanda Seyfried

quote_original: I felt a tremendous sadness for men who can't deal with a woman of their own age.
author: Michael Caine

quote_original: Revenge is the naked idol of the worship of a semi-barbarous age.
author: Percy Bysshe Shelley

quote_original: I think I don't regret a single 'excess' of my responsive youth - I only regret, in my chilled age, certain occasions and possibilities I didn't embrace.
author: Henry James

quote_original: Our Age of Anxiety is, in great part, the result of trying to do today's job with yesterday's tools and yesterday's concepts.
author: Marshall McLuhan

quote_original: I'll tell you, there is nothing better in life than being a late bloomer. I believe that success can happen at any time and at any age.
author: Salma Hayek

quote_original: Man arrives as a novice at each age of his life.
author: Nicolas Chamfort

quote_original: Live your life and forget your age.
author: Jean Paul

quote_original: I can't look in the mirror and look at fake things. I just can't. I'd rather age.
author: Heidi Klum

quote_original: The surest sign of age is loneliness.
author: Annie Dillard

quote_original: Learning to dislike children at an early age saves a lot of expense and aggravation later in life.
author: Robert Byrne

quote_original: Confidence is something you're born with. I know I had loads of it even at the age of 15.
author: Hedy Lamarr

quote_original: We accumulate our opinions at an age when our understanding is at its weakest.
author: Georg C. Lichtenberg

quote_original: I got to experience soccer at the highest level at a young age I decided I wanted to be part of that for as long as possible.
author: Mia Hamm

quote_original: Living in an age of advertisement, we are perpetually disillusioned. The perfect life is spread before us every day, but it changes and withers at a touch.
author: J. B. Priestley

quote_original: Age, like distance lends a double charm.
author: Oliver Herford

quote_original: Utility is the great idol of the age, to which all powers must do service and all talents swear allegiance.
author: Friedrich Schiller

quote_original: Anyone who writes an autobiographical work at the age of 34 is, at best, presumptuous. It occurred to me that it was time to set the record straight.
author: Jessica Savitch

quote_original: New needs need new techniques. And the modern artists have found new ways and new means of making their statements... the modern painter cannot express this age, the airplane, the atom bomb, the radio, in the old forms of the Renaissance or of any other past culture.
author: Jackson Pollock

quote_original: One of the tough things about being an actor, probably the hardest thing, is getting your foot in the door, and my father handled that for me at a very early age.
author: Jeff Bridges

quote_original: Any role that big is going to be a challenge for any actor, but for an actor of a young age, it's going to be even tougher.
author: Jeff Bridges

quote_original: Now is the age of anxiety.
author: W. H. Auden

quote_original: I think it's pretty crazy to say you've been typecast at the age of 20 before you've even really started getting going.
author: Tom Felton

quote_original: At the age of four with paper hats and wooden swords we're all Generals. Only some of us never grow out of it.
author: Peter Ustinov

quote_original: My inspiration was my mom. She's a great cook, and she still cooks, and we still banter back and forth about cooking. Growing up in a mostly Portuguese community, food was important and the family table was extremely important. At a very young age I understood that.
author: Emeril Lagasse

quote_original: The great book for you is the book that has the most to say to you at the moment when you are reading. I do not mean the book that is most instructive, but the book that feeds your spirit. And that depends on your age, your experience, your psychological and spiritual need.
author: Robertson Davies

quote_original: Age gives you a great sense of proportion. You can be very hard on yourself when you're younger but now I just think 'well everybody's absolutely mad and I'm doing quite well'.
author: Steven Morrissey

quote_original: If the nineteenth century was the age of the editorial chair, ours is the century of the psychiatrist's couch.
author: Marshall McLuhan

quote_original: American youth attributes much more importance to arriving at driver's license age than at voting age.
author: Marshall McLuhan

quote_original: I think a child should be allowed to take his father's or mother's name at will on coming of age. Paternity is a legal fiction.
author: James Joyce

quote_original: Old age is the most unexpected of all things that happen to a man.
author: Leon Trotsky

quote_original: You get to a certain age where you prepare yourself for happiness. Sometimes you never remember to actually get happy.
author: John Mayer

quote_original: Being a father at a later age is different from when I had my other two daughters when I was in my 20s and 30s. If you're in your 60s and you're with the kid every day, you're dealing with the mind of a child, so it opens up that childishness in you again.
author: Martin Scorsese

quote_original: A moment comes, which comes but rarely in history, when we step out from the old to the new when an age ends and when the soul of a nation long suppressed finds utterance.
author: Jawaharlal Nehru

quote_original: There is nothing in socialism that a little age or a little money will not cure.
author: Will Durant

quote_original: If you age with somebody, you go through so many roles - you're lovers, friends, enemies, colleagues, strangers you're brother and sister. That's what intimacy is, if you're with your soulmate.
author: Cate Blanchett

quote_original: With age, you see people fail more. You see yourself fail more. How do you keep that fearlessness of a kid? You keep going. Luckily, I'm not afraid to make a fool of myself.
author: Hugh Jackman

quote_original: I'm not skinny for the wrong reasons. It's not because I'm bulimic or anorexic or doing drugs. Compared to a lot of actresses my age, I'm actually overweight.
author: Lindsay Lohan

quote_original: It seems that when you get to a certain age you almost give yourself permission to misbehave and say what you think. People allow it, with very old people.
author: Julie Walters

quote_original: I'm not as far along as Jack Nicklaus was at this age, but I'm trying.
author: Tiger Woods

quote_original: When superstition is allowed to perform the task of old age in dulling the human temperament, we can say goodbye to all excellence in poetry, in painting, and in music.
author: Denis Diderot

quote_original: Peace is the one condition of survival in this nuclear age.
author: Adlai E. Stevenson

quote_original: What could be more beautiful than a dear old lady growing wise with age? Every age can be enchanting, provided you live within it.
author: Brigitte Bardot

quote_original: You'd think that in this age, especially in the 21st century - especially with all the technology and all the discoveries that we've made - that we would figure out how to tackle abuse.
author: Tori Amos

quote_original: Here comes 40. I'm feeling my age and I've ordered the Ferrari. I'm going to get the whole mid-life crisis package.
author: Keanu Reeves

quote_original: At a young age winning is not the most important thing... the important thing is to develop creative and skilled players with good confidence.
author: Arsene Wenger

quote_original: We live in an age where the artist is forgotten. He is a researcher. I see myself that way.
author: David Hockney

quote_original: I lived the true American dream, because I was able to pursue what I set as my goals at a very young age.
author: Mario Andretti

quote_original: Everybody looks like clones and the only people you notice are my age. I don't notice anybody unless they look great, and every now and again they do, and they are usually 70.
author: Vivienne Westwood

quote_original: Photography suits the temper of this age - of active bodies and minds. It is a perfect medium for one whose mind is teeming with ideas, imagery, for a prolific worker who would be slowed down by painting or sculpting, for one who sees quickly and acts decisively, accurately.
author: Edward Weston

quote_original: I never - you know also one of the things that would save me for a man my age, it was not that easy to lose that much weight and fall down and look like something draped.
author: Karl Lagerfeld

quote_original: I wish I'd gotten sober at a younger age.
author: Janice Dickinson

quote_original: Middle Age is that perplexing time of life when we hear two voices calling us, one saying, 'Why not?' and the other, 'Why bother?'
author: Sydney J. Harris

quote_original: Save your money. You're going to need twice as much money in your old age as you think.
author: Michael Caine

quote_original: If you read back in the Bible, the letter of the apostle Paul to the church of Thessalonia, he said that in the latter days before the end of the age that the Earth would be caught up in what he called the birth pangs of a new order.
author: Pat Robertson

quote_original: There is no self-knowledge but an historical one. No one knows what he himself is who does not know his fellow men, especially the most prominent one of the community, the master's master, the genius of the age.
author: Karl Wilhelm Friedrich Schlegel

quote_original: Middle age is when your old classmates are so grey and wrinkled and bald they don't recognize you.
author: Bennett Cerf

quote_original: In this electronic age we see ourselves being translated more and more into the form of information, moving toward the technological extension of consciousness.
author: Marshall McLuhan

quote_original: You can judge your age by the amount of pain you feel when you come in contact with a new idea.
author: Pearl S. Buck

quote_original: The sanitary and mechanical age we are now entering makes up for the mercy it grants to our sense of smell by the ferocity with which it assails our sense of hearing.
author: Havelock Ellis

quote_original: Middle age is when you've met so many people that every new person you meet reminds you of someone else.
author: Ogden Nash

quote_original: There are people whose watch stops at a certain hour and who remain permanently at that age.
author: Helen Rowland

quote_original: My justification is that most people my age spend a lot of time thinking about what they're going to do for the next five or ten years. The time they spend thinking about their life, I just spend drinking.
author: Amy Winehouse

quote_original: They that have lived a single day have lived an age.
author: Jean de la Bruyere

quote_original: From the age of fifteen, dogma has been the fundamental principle of my religion: I know no other religion I cannot enter into the idea of any other sort of religion religion, as a mere sentiment, is to me a dream and a mockery.
author: John Henry Newman

quote_original: The class distinctions proper to a democratic society are not those of rank or money, still less, as is apt to happen when these are abandoned, of race, but of age.
author: W. H. Auden

quote_original: Old age, calm, expanded, broad with the haughty breadth of the universe, old age flowing free with the delicious near-by freedom of death.
author: Edith Wharton

quote_original: We are living in the machine age. For the first time in history the comedian has been compelled to supply himself with jokes and comedy material to compete with the machine. Whether he knows it or not, the comedian is on a treadmill to oblivion.
author: Fred Allen

quote_original: At a certain age it just became apparent to me that this was probably the work that I would have to do.
author: Daniel Day-Lewis

quote_original: Genius is present in every age, but the men carrying it within them remain benumbed unless extraordinary events occur to heat up and melt the mass so that it flows forth.
author: Denis Diderot

quote_original: Every age needs men who will redeem the time by living with a vision of the things that are to be.
author: Adlai E. Stevenson

quote_original: I would like to see more airplay for all artists, no matter what age. I think there's a lot of money being spent toward the young guys, but a lot of the older guys are the ones who blazed the trail for those young guys.
author: Willie Nelson

quote_original: In my old age, I'll be in L.A.
author: David Hockney

quote_original: I shall not grow conservative with age.
author: Elizabeth Cady Stanton

quote_original: I first learned that there were black people living in some place called other than the United States in the western hemisphere when I was a very little boy, and my father told me that when he was a boy about my age, he wanted to be an Episcopal priest, because he so admired his priest, a black man from someplace called Haiti.
author: Henry Louis Gates

quote_original: Why should 20-year-olds only be considered sexy? I think we get better with age.
author: Jenny McCarthy

quote_original: I saw how many people were poor and how many kids my age went to school hungry in the morning, which I don't think most of my contemporaries in racially segregated schools in the South thought very much about at the time.
author: Charles Kuralt

quote_original: When you get to my age life seems little more than one long march to and from the lavatory.
author: A. C. Benson

quote_original: I think, if you put a camera in anyone's life and document it daily from the age of 21 to 27, there are going to be things that aren't always pretty.
author: Sienna Miller

quote_original: Non-disclosure in the Internet Age is quickly perceived as a breach of trust. Government, corporations and each of us as individuals must recalibrate how we live and share our lives appropriate to the information now available and the expectations of others.
author: Simon Mainwaring

quote_original: Where children are, there is the golden age.
author: Novalis

quote_original: Sure I played, did you think I was born at the age of 70 sitting in a dugout trying to manage guys like you?
author: Casey Stengel

quote_original: To be free in an age like ours, one must be in a position of authority. That in itself would be enough to make me ambitious.
author: Hannah Arendt

quote_original: I came to water late. I learned to swim at the age of 20.
author: Liam Neeson

quote_original: People are so busy dreaming the American Dream, fantasizing about what they could be or have a right to be, that they're all asleep at the switch. Consequently we are living in the Age of Human Error.
author: Florence King

quote_original: I was getting hot flashes and sweats on a regular basis. That's not normal, even for my age.
author: Kareem Abdul-Jabbar

quote_original: I remember at the age of five travelling on a trolley car with my mother past a group of women on a picket line at a textile plant, seeing them being viciously beaten by security people. So that kind of thing stayed with me.
author: Noam Chomsky

quote_original: Age is not all decay it is the ripening, the swelling, of the fresh life within, that withers and bursts the husk.
author: George MacDonald

quote_original: I knew at a young age, whether I was playing baseball or hockey or lacrosse, that my teammates were counting on me, whether it be to strike the last batter out in a baseball game or score a big goal in a hockey game.
author: Wayne Gretzky

quote_original: The funniest racism is the racism between minorities. It's something you don't see dramatized, but almost every minority I know who's my age, they have these funny stories about their parents stereotyping other minorities.
author: Mindy Kaling

quote_original: It's ironic that at age 32, at probably the greatest moment of my career, with The Godfather having such an enormous success, I wasn't even aware of it, because I was somewhere else under the deadline again.
author: Francis Ford Coppola

quote_original: I'm asked all the time in interviews about who I am, and I know a few people my age who have a strong sense of self, but I couldn't say I know myself and sum it up and give it to you in a little package. I don't know myself at all yet.
author: Kristen Stewart

quote_original: Alexander at the head of the world never tasted the true pleasure that boys of his own age have enjoyed at the head of a school.
author: Horace Walpole

quote_original: To separate children from others of similar age and qualifications solely because of their race generates a feeling of inferiority as to their status in the community that may affect their hearts and minds in a way unlikely ever to be undone.
author: Earl Warren

quote_original: In an age of incompetence, I've been able to last in this crazy business. I actually know how to play my ax and write a song. That's my job.
author: Billy Joel

quote_original: In this age of media and Internet access, we are much more talkative than ever before.
author: David Duchovny

quote_original: Over the years Woodstock got glorified and romanticised and became the event that symbolised Utopia. It's the last page of our collective memory of the age of innocence. Then things turned ugly and would never be the same again.
author: Ang Lee

quote_original: Every time I see something terrible, it's like I see it at age 19. I keep a freshness that way.
author: Ralph Nader

quote_original: I hate to mention age, but I come from an era when we weren't consumed by technology and television.
author: Jimmy Buffett

quote_original: We are approaching a new age of synthesis. Knowledge cannot be merely a degree or a skill... it demands a broader vision, capabilities in critical thinking and logical deduction without which we cannot have constructive progress.
author: Li Ka Shing

quote_original: Morality comes with the sad wisdom of age, when the sense of curiosity has withered.
author: Graham Greene

quote_original: Every age yearns for a more beautiful world. The deeper the desperation and the depression about the confusing present, the more intense that yearning.
author: Johan Huizinga

quote_original: To be told that one can be dependent on one's parents until age 26 should strike a young person who wants to grow up as demeaning, not as something to celebrate.
author: Dennis Prager

quote_original: Does age matter? Time doesn't matter.
author: Sandra Bullock

quote_original: I figured out it was a social thing, what women were allowed to do. At a very young age, I decided I was not going to follow women's rules.
author: Joan Jett

quote_original: We were really grown up for our age and it was an incredible special band.
author: Joan Jett

quote_original: Age is the first limitation on roles that I've ever had to encounter, and I hit that awhile ago.
author: Jack Nicholson

quote_original: I can't hit on women in public any more. I didn't decide this it just doesn't feel right at my age.
author: Jack Nicholson

quote_original: This is the first age that's ever paid much attention to the future, which is a little ironic since we may not have one.
author: Arthur C. Clarke

quote_original: I feel we live in the kind of culture now where you have to be very smart to navigate the right way, and I just don't have those smarts. I think with age and time it will change, but I can't obsess about it.
author: Sienna Miller

quote_original: The secret of long life is double careers. One to about age sixty, then another for the next thirty years.
author: David Ogilvy

quote_original: I knew at an early age I wanted to act. Acting was always easy for me. I don't believe in predestination, but I do believe that once you get where ever it is you are going, that is where you were going to be.
author: Morgan Freeman

quote_original: The age in which we live, this non-stop distraction, is making it more impossible for the young generation to ever have the curiosity or discipline... because you need to be alone to find out anything.
author: Vivienne Westwood

quote_original: I can feel the 60S looming. In my profession, I've just moved along with my age. By thinking in decades, rather than whether someone's 42 or 47, you can give yourself a whole 10 years to turn yourself around in.
author: Francesca Annis

quote_original: We all know now that people can look good for their age. It isn't so extraordinary, I don't know why people go on about it so much.
author: Francesca Annis

quote_original: A lot of music you might listen to is pretty vapid, it doesn't always deal with our deeper issues. These are the things I'm interested in now, particularly at my age.
author: Annie Lennox

quote_original: Life expectancy in many parts of Africa can be something around the age of thirty five to thirty eight. I mean you're very fortunate if you live to that age. In fact when I went to Uganda for the first time one of the things that occurred to me was that I saw very few elderly people.
author: Annie Lennox

quote_original: Light and funny has a more compelling quality when you're younger. But I haven't abandoned the genre: I love falling down I love Lucille Ball. It's just that a lot of those stories revolve around problems that I can't convincingly portray at this age.
author: Julia Roberts

quote_original: I had the good fortune to be able to right an injustice that I thought was being heaped on young people by lowering the voting age, where you had young people that were old enough to die in Vietnam but not old enough to vote for their members of Congress that sent them there.
author: Birch Bayh

quote_original: The value of old age depends upon the person who reaches it. To some men of early performance it is useless. To others, who are late to develop, it just enables them to finish the job.
author: Thomas Hardy

quote_original: I've gotten crankier in my old age.
author: Shirley MacLaine

quote_original: I've been very competitive by nature from a young age, whether it was eating a bowl of pasta faster than somebody else, or always wanting to be the first one in line.
author: Maria Sharapova

quote_original: Death comes not to the living soul, nor age to the loving heart.
author: Phoebe Cary

quote_original: I'm not busy... a woman with three children under the age of 10 wouldn't think my schedule looked so busy.
author: Garrison Keillor

quote_original: High expectations weren't nurtured in my neck of nowhere back then - children weren't fawned over from an early age as 'gifted' and groomed for a prizewinning future self-esteem was considered something you had to pick from the garden yourself.
author: James Wolcott

quote_original: Not by age but by capacity is wisdom acquired.
author: Plautus

quote_original: Whoever marries the spirit of this age will find himself a widower in the next.
author: William Ralph Inge

quote_original: Of middle age the best that can be said is that a middle-aged person has likely learned how to have a little fun in spite of his troubles.
author: Don Marquis

quote_original: Old age is always wakeful as if, the longer linked with life, the less man has to do with aught that looks like death.
author: Herman Melville

quote_original: What I think is amazing is not that 85% of people who get married under the age of 25 get divorced, it's that 15% of them stay together. How did they manage to pull that off? You almost can't wait too long. It's the single simplest measure to predict divorce.
author: Elizabeth Gilbert

quote_original: I avoid talking before the youth of the age as I would dancing before them: for if one's tongue don't move in the steps of the day, and thinks to please by its old graces, it is only an object of ridicule.
author: Horace Walpole

quote_original: I'm glad I was born when I was. My time was the golden age of variety. If I were starting out again now, maybe things would happen for me, but it certainly would not be on a variety show with 28 musicians, 12 dancers, two major guest stars, 50 costumes a week by Bob Mackie. The networks just wouldn't spend the money today.
author: Carol Burnett

quote_original: I was taught from a young age that many people would treat me as a second-class citizen because I was African-American and because I was female.
author: Queen Latifah

quote_original: Even from a very early age, I knew I didn't want to miss out on anything life had to offer just because it might be considered dangerous.
author: Nicole Kidman

quote_original: We live in an age where anonymity is growing in magnitude like a bomb going off.
author: Jock Sturges

quote_original: I was a mixture of being incredibly old for my age and incredibly backwards. I was born quite old, but then I stopped growing. I lived with my mum and dad till I was 30.
author: Helena Bonham Carter

quote_original: The Word of fire burns today On the lips of our prophets in an evil age.
author: Margaret Walker

quote_original: What is wrong with the Iranians in addition to the nuclear bomb? This is the only country on Earth in the 21st century that has renewed imperialistic ambitions. They really want to become the hegemon of the Middle East in an age that gave up imperialism.

quote_original: I think it's quite extraordinary that people cast me as if I'm Warren Beatty: until I met my present wife, at the age of 35, you could name two girlfriends.

quote_original: Craziest thing I've done for love is getting married. I think it's crazy. I think it's crazy, crazy, crazy. I'm never going to say I wouldn't do it again but I have to make sure it's love and not settling for the 'I have to do this by a certain age,' which is kind of what I did.

quote_original: You never choose the way that you're raised, it's just the way that you were raised, but you do get to a certain age where you're in a position to question the expectations of you and the way that you've been formed by your surroundings.

quote_original: We tried not to age, but time had its rage.

quote_original: I want to age with some dignity.

quote_original: This is my 20th year in the sport. I've known swimming and that's it. I don't want to swim past age 30 if I continue after this Olympics, and come back in 2016, I'll be 31. I'm looking forward to being able to see the other side of the fence.
author: Michael Phelps

quote_original: Young man, the secret of my success is that an early age I discovered that I was not God.
author: Oliver Wendell Holmes, Jr.

quote_original: I'd like to talk about free markets. Information in the computer age is the last genuine free market left on earth except those free markets where indigenous people are still surviving. And that's basically becoming limited.
author: Russell Means

quote_original: I would often find myself, at the age of 21, at midnight, running down a dark street on my own with 10 men chasing me. And the fact they had cameras in their hands made that legal.

quote_original: Bring a wife home to your house when you are of the right age, not far short of 30 years, nor much above this is the right time for marriage.
author: Hesiod

quote_original: There are only two things a child will share willingly communicable diseases and its mother's age.
author: Benjamin Spock

quote_original: Although it is generally known, I think it's about time to announce that I was born at a very early age.
author: Douglas Horton

quote_original: I think it's your mental attitude. So many of us start dreading age in high school and that's a waste of a lovely life. 'Oh... I'm 30, oh, I'm 40, oh, 50.' Make the most of it.

quote_original: No, no, I was only funny on stage, really. I, I, think I was funny as a person toward my classmates when I was very young. You know, when I was a child, up to about the age of 12.
author: Rowan Atkinson

quote_original: What goes on in Europe concerns us greatly because, if Europe comes apart, the E.U. comes apart, then you're going to have enormous impact on America, that's a very big trading partner of ours, and people own securities around the world in this day and age.
author: Michael Bloomberg

quote_original: Your body actually reminds you about your age and your injuries - the body has a stronger memory than your mind.
author: Mikhail Baryshnikov

quote_original: People dance at any age.
author: Mikhail Baryshnikov

quote_original: I never had little brothers, so I was totally not used to hearing a lot of cussing at a young age! I learned what 'pull my finger' meant the hard way.
author: Danica McKellar

quote_original: My sister and I shared a bedroom our entire lives and I believe she discovered the Beatles when she was about 11 and I'm four years younger. author: Christina Ricci

quote_original: But look, I was born in 1956, the peak year for births in US history. I think I'm very representative of many of the thought processes my generation have been through and, by and large, people of my age have had their imprint planted on the consciousness of western society for a long time.
author: Tom Hanks

quote_original: I basically get stereotyped a lot in terms of being a girl and writing 'chick' music for teenage girls or something. I think, if anything, the press kind of, because of my gender and my age, tends to kind of relegate my work to this sort of special-interest group. It's part of the cultural dynamic, I guess.
author: Ani DiFranco

quote_original: What is amazing for a woman of my age is that I change as the world is changing-and changing very, very fast. I don't think my mother had that opportunity to change.
author: Jeanne Moreau

quote_original: I've never worried about age.
author: Jeanne Moreau

quote_original: To me age is a number, just a number. Who cares?
author: Jeanne Moreau

quote_original: If you're extremely, painfully frightened of age, it shows.
author: Jeanne Moreau

quote_original: For a man who has compared himself to Theodore Roosevelt and the nation's challenges to those of the Gilded Age, Obama put forward a tepid agenda.
author: Ron Fournier

quote_original: I wrote a screenplay for a 'Sweet Valley High' adaptation, and it's really amazing to me how many women who are my age have responded to the idea and are excited about the movie.
