quote_original: I think about dying. I've come to realize we all die alone in one way or another.
author: Richard Pryor

quote_original: Because for whatever reason, even though I want to stay home all the time and be left alone, I want to tell the world who I am now.
author: Fiona Apple

quote_original: I love the solitude of being on a plane and finally getting to read an entire book and being left alone.

quote_original: I don't think I ever got the hang of the writers' room. I love collaborating with people, but I really do my best work alone, and I think I would want to - if I did something again, I think I'd want to take total ownership the way Aaron Sorkin or David Kelley does.
author: Diablo Cody

quote_original: Fear of error which everything recalls to me at every moment of the flight of my ideas, this mania for control, makes men prefer reason's imagination to the imagination of the senses. And yet it is always the imagination alone which is at work.

quote_original: Work, apart from devotion or love of God, is helpless and cannot stand alone.
author: Ramakrishna

quote_original: I was never less alone than when by myself.
author: Edward Gibbon

quote_original: The attempt to devote oneself to literature alone is a most deceptive thing, and often, paradoxically, it is literature that suffers for it.
author: Vaclav Havel

quote_original: Our future cannot depend on the government alone. The ultimate solutions lie in the attitudes and the actions of the American people.
author: Joe Biden

quote_original: People talk about the conscience, but it seems to me one must just bring it up to a certain point and leave it there. You can let your conscience alone if you're nice to the second housemaid.
author: Henry James

quote_original: Those who remember Washington's cold war culture in the 1980s will recall the shocked reactions to Reagan's intervention. People interested in foreign policy were astonished when in 1985 he met alone at Geneva - alone, not a single strategic thinker at his elbow! - with the Soviet Communist master Gorbachev.
author: Russell Baker

quote_original: Palin was a political Hail Mary, a long bomb in the closing minutes of a game that John McCain and Co. were certain to lose. They didn't care if she had the policy or political or emotional capacity to serve as vice president, let alone president. They were willing to drive the country off a cliff, if that's what it took to win.
author: Dee Dee Myers

quote_original: This, and this alone, is Christianity, a universal holiness in every part of life, a heavenly wisdom in all our actions, not conforming to the spirit and temper of the world but turning all worldly enjoyments into means of piety and devotion to God.
author: William Law

quote_original: The Fuhrer alone is the present and future German reality and its law. Learn to know ever more deeply: from now on every single thing demands decision, and every action responsibility.
author: Martin Heidegger

quote_original: Fail I alone, in words and deeds? Why, all men strive and who succeeds?
author: Robert Browning

quote_original: Finds progress, man's distinctive mark alone, Not God's, and not the beast's God is, they are, Man partly is, and wholly hopes to be.
author: Robert Browning

quote_original: Liberal that I am, I support health-care reform on its merits alone. My liberal blood boils, for example, when I read that half of the personal bankruptcies in this country are brought on, in part, by medical expenses.
author: Thomas Frank

quote_original: I don't think nationalism is alone holding the field it's in contention with a lot of different things.
author: Peter Singer

quote_original: I am alone, some people help me, but, basically, I can do what I want.
author: Sergei Bubka

quote_original: I mean, I don't think I'm alone when I look at the homeless person or the bum or the psychotic or the drunk or the drug addict or the criminal and see their baby pictures in my mind's eye. You don't think they were cute like every other baby?

quote_original: It is the unknown that excites the ardor of scholars, who, in the known alone, would shrivel up with boredom.
author: Wallace Stevens

quote_original: Most high courts in other nations do not have discretion, such as we enjoy, in selecting the cases that the high court reviews. Our court is virtually alone in the amount of discretion it has.
author: Sandra Day O'Connor

quote_original: Yes, I will bring the understanding of a woman to the Court, but I doubt that alone will affect my decisions.
author: Sandra Day O'Connor

quote_original: With production alone as the goal, industry in North America was dominated by the assembly line, standardization for mass consumption.
author: Arthur Erickson

quote_original: The music industry is a strange combination of having real and intangible assets: pop bands are brand names in themselves, and at a given stage in their careers their name alone can practically gaurantee hit records.
author: Richard Branson

quote_original: It would do the world good if every man would compel himself occasionally to be absolutely alone. Most of the world s progress has come out of such loneliness.
author: Bruce Barton

quote_original: And if you don't believe the sun will rise, stand alone and greet the coming night in the last remaining light.
author: Chris Cornell

quote_original: A celibate, like the fly in the heart of an apple, dwells in a perpetual sweetness, but sits alone, and is confined and dies in singularity.
author: Jeremy Taylor

quote_original: He alone is free who lives with free consent under the entire guidance of reason.
author: Baruch Spinoza

quote_original: Only that thing is free which exists by the necessities of its own nature, and is determined in its actions by itself alone.
author: Baruch Spinoza

quote_original: Wisdom alone is true ambition's aim, wisdom is the source of virtue and of fame obtained with labour, for mankind employed, and then, when most you share it, best enjoyed.
author: Alfred North Whitehead

quote_original: My contribution I hope is to get people to eat full-flavored food. If I could come away with that alone, that would be a fantastic accomplishment. I'm also very proud of being a very American chef.

quote_original: But no nation can base its survival and development on luck and prayers alone while its leadership fritters away every available opportunity for success and concrete achievement.

quote_original: Solitude is strength to depend on the presence of the crowd is weakness. The man who needs a mob to nerve him is much more alone than he imagines.
author: Paul Brunton

quote_original: He was thinking alone, and seriously racking his brain to find a direction for this single force four times multiplied, with which he did not doubt, as with the lever for which Archimedes sought, they should succeed in moving the world, when some one tapped gently at his door.
author: Alexandre Dumas

quote_original: When I decided to be a singer, my mother warned me I'd be alone a lot. Basically we all are.

quote_original: And remember don't high post when you're far from home, and high posting when you're all alone.

quote_original: Go on thinking that you don't need to be read and you'll find that it may become quite true: no one will feel the need tom read it because it is written for yourself alone and the public won't feel any impulse to gate crash such a private party.

quote_original: Being alone is scarier than any boogey man and the reason why I don't choose to see Horror movies as a rule.
author: Tom Sizemore

quote_original: I have been alone since my husband died. I stay in my home. I don't date. It's hard to date when you're at home. Nobody knows you.

quote_original: I'd like to state that Spike Lee is not saying that African American culture is just for black people alone to enjoy and cherish. Culture is for everybody.
author: Spike Lee

quote_original: Once a disease has entered the body, all parts which are healthy must fight it: not one alone, but all. Because a disease might mean their common death. Nature knows this and Nature attacks the disease with whatever help she can muster.

quote_original: The progress of evolution from President Washington to President Grant was alone evidence to upset Darwin.
author: Henry Adams

quote_original: I'm the most gregarious of men and love good company, but never less alone when alone.
author: Peter O'Toole

quote_original: The daily act of writing remains as demanding and maddening as it was before, and the pleasure you get from writing - rare but profound - remains at the true heart of the enterprise. On their best days, writers all over the world are winning Pulitzers, all alone in their studios, with no one watching.
author: Jeffrey Eugenides

quote_original: Costumes and scenery alone will not attract audiences.
author: Anna Held

quote_original: There are times when the only access I have to the truest person that I am is when I'm alone and trying to solve a sentence. It's exciting, even when it's frustrating, even when I can't do it right.
author: Elizabeth Gilbert

quote_original: Well, I'm not a member of the permanent political establishment, and I've learned quickly these last few days that if you're not a member in good standing of the Washington elite, then some in the media consider a candidate unqualified for that reason alone.
author: Sarah Palin

quote_original: Successful crimes alone are justified.
author: John Dryden

quote_original: Volume depends precisely on the writer's having been able to sit in a room every day, year after year, alone.
author: Susan Sontag

quote_original: Still, intuitive assumptions about behavior is only the starting point of systematic analysis, for alone they do not yield many interesting implications.
author: Gary Becker

quote_original: The writer is all alone.
author: V. S. Naipaul

quote_original: If you write a novel alone you sit and you weave a little narrative. And it's O.K., but it's of no account.
author: V. S. Naipaul

quote_original: There is no end to the violations committed by children on children, quietly talking alone.
author: Elizabeth Bowen

quote_original: Never to lie is to have no lock on your door, you are never wholly alone.
author: Elizabeth Bowen

quote_original: Muslims must believe that all power, success and victory comes from God alone.
author: Abu Bakar Bashir

quote_original: If man knew how women pass the time when they are alone, they'd never marry.

quote_original: I don't like being alone.
author: Cristiano Ronaldo

quote_original: You can be around 100 people and be completely alone. People don't realize what it's really like.

quote_original: That we find a crystal or a poppy beautiful means that we are less alone, that we are more deeply inserted into existence than the course of a single life would lead us to believe.
author: John Berger

quote_original: One of the places where we lived when I was growing up had this big wood out the back. And starting when I was about 8, I used to enjoy just walking alone through the wood late. Eleven p.m. Midnight. Later.

quote_original: Others indeed may talk, and write, and fight about liberty, and make an outward pretence to it but the free-thinker alone is truly free.
author: George Berkeley

quote_original: Writers may be disreputable, incorrigible, early to decay or late to bloom but they dare to go it alone.
author: John Updike

quote_original: I love my government not least for the extent to which it leaves me alone.
author: John Updike

quote_original: For every quarrel a man and wife have before others, they have a hundred when alone.
author: E. W. Howe

quote_original: I'm not someone who likes to have my picture taken, let alone see it plastered all over the place.
author: Laura Linney

quote_original: Benevolence alone will not make a teacher, nor will learning alone do it. The gift of teaching is a peculiar talent, and implies a need and a craving in the teacher himself.
author: John Jay Chapman

quote_original: It's important to say that actors can't act alone, it's impossible. What we have to do is support each other.

quote_original: In the laughing times we know that we are lucky, and in the quiet times we know that we are blessed. And we will not be alone.
author: Dar Williams

quote_original: The flesh endures the storms of the present alone the mind, those of the past and future as well as the present. Gluttony is a lust of the mind.
author: Thomas Hobbes

quote_original: Every animal leaves traces of what it was man alone leaves traces of what he created.
author: Jacob Bronowski

quote_original: The only way to get gay issues off the front pages of Canadian newspapers is to grant gay and lesbian people our full civil equality and leave it alone.

quote_original: I do not come bearing a party label on my sleeve - or a quick fix in my back pocket. I do not come with a rigid ideology in my heart - or a soul that tells me to go it alone. I do not come to uproot tradition - or to be imprisoned by it.

quote_original: I'm a grown woman and sometimes, I might be a little fat, you know? Am I alone there? Not really.

quote_original: From 18 to 22, I was alone, living in L.A. with a bunch of friends, partying.

quote_original: We talk a lot on 'Biggest Loser' about how fitness is a natural antidepressant, how it burns off stress. What I like about running is that it gives me time alone. I'm always busy, with people at work, with my kids. I love getting out for a run by myself and just listening to my music.

quote_original: Britain, relative to the U.S., is a highly secular society. Philanthropy alone cannot fill the gap left by government cutbacks. And the sources of altruism go deep into our evolutionary past.
author: Jonathan Sacks

quote_original: As a young man, even if I was going to see a play or a film by myself, I didn't feel like I was alone. There was something that was unfolding up there that brought me into it. And I recognised that. For those two hours, it made me feel like I belonged to something really good.
author: Tom Hanks

quote_original: Solitude, though it may be silent as light, is like light, the mightiest of agencies for solitude is essential to man. All men come into this world alone and leave it alone.

quote_original: Most of these people who are celebrities now don't do anything to deserve it, so by that fact alone, I don't want to be one.
author: will.i.am

quote_original: Men don't even ask me out. I can't remember the last time I was asked out on a date, and I'm talking years here. I spend my life more and more alone.

quote_original: I couldn't even go to the bathroom alone. My mother or a social worker always went with me.
author: Natalie Wood

quote_original: I wrote and produced millions and millions of selling records, so my publishing company alone was worth millions of dollars. I didn't have to work anymore in life because when the rappers started sampling... I'm the most sampled artist in history.
author: Rick James

quote_original: I would hope that understanding and reconciliation are not limited to the 19th hole alone.
author: Gerald R. Ford

quote_original: I'm not at the point where I'd feel safe in a house alone. I would be really scared. I'm the kind of person that when I get up to go use the bathroom I have this big long hallway, and I just know someone's going to jump out and get me.
author: Britney Spears

quote_original: To be adult is to be alone.
author: Jean Rostand

quote_original: I'm not a rock star. Sure I am, to a certain extent because of the situation, but when kids ask me how it feels to be a rock star, I say leave me alone, I'm not a rock star. I'm not in it for the fame, I'm in it because I like to play.

quote_original: I may be alone in this, but I do sense the power of film, in that movies have the ability to literally change people's minds. That's pretty powerful stuff when you consider that.
author: Nicolas Cage

quote_original: The thing I like about baseball is that it's one-on-one. You stand up there alone, and if you make a mistake, it's your mistake. If you hit a home run, it's your home run.
author: Hank Aaron

quote_original: In the first 50 years of the filibuster, it was used only 35 times. But the last Congress alone had 112 cloture motions filed, plus threats of more. This is the tyranny of the minority.
author: Peter Fenn

quote_original: Perhaps our own opposition to even the level of European integration we have now, let alone any more, is well known.
author: Nigel Farage

quote_original: My learning process is by eye alone it's not at all scientific.
author: Miuccia Prada

quote_original: As a child, I wanted only two things - to be left alone to read my library books, and to get away from my provincial hometown and go to London to be a writer. And I always knew that when I got there, I wanted to make loads of money.
author: Julie Burchill

quote_original: Surely being a Professional Beauty - let alone an ageing one - is one of the most insecure and doomed careers imaginable.
author: Julie Burchill

quote_original: But we cannot rely on memorials and museums alone. We can tell ourselves we will never forget and we likely won't. But we need to make sure that we teach history to those who never had the opportunity to remember in the first place.
author: Dan Rather

quote_original: I feel so good after a workout. Any time you can be alone with yourself is really important.
author: Shay Mitchell

quote_original: I tried acupuncture, the patch, and hypnosis, but found that I needed to do it alone - when the time was right for me.
author: Christy Turlington

quote_original: I think sometimes if you are alone, you are freer because your time is your own.
author: Aung San Suu Kyi

quote_original: One person alone can't do anything as important as bringing genuine democracy to a country.
author: Aung San Suu Kyi

quote_original: No one should be left to suffer alone.
author: Daisaku Ikeda

quote_original: When you work alone, you need to socialize at some level.
author: Jeffery Deaver

quote_original: I must try and break through the cliches about Latin America. Superpowers and other outsiders have fought over us for centuries in ways that have nothing to do with our problems. In reality we are all alone.
author: Gabriel Garcia Marquez

quote_original: The right to be let alone is indeed the beginning of all freedoms.
author: William O. Douglas

quote_original: Yeah, my dream would be to work for 6 months and then have 6 months to play, just snowboarding, surfing, and going to cool places to listen and be alone and kinda chill out.
author: Marc Newson

quote_original: Making checklists of things you're looking for in a person is the numero uno thing you can do to guarantee you'll be alone forever.
author: Joseph Gordon-Levitt

quote_original: I'm a very brave person. I can go to North Vietnam, I can challenge my government, but I can't challenge the man I'm with if means I'm going to end up alone.
author: Jane Fonda

quote_original: When the traveler goes alone he gets acquainted with himself.
author: Liberty Hyde Bailey

quote_original: At the root of the shy temperament is a deep fear of social judgment, one so severe it can sometimes be crippling. Introverted people don't worry unduly about whether they'll be found wanting, they just find too much socializing exhausting and would prefer either to be alone or in the company of a select few people.
author: Jeffrey Kluger

quote_original: Virtue alone has majesty in death.
author: Edward Young

quote_original: Probably nothing serious or worthwhile can be accomplished without one's willingness to be alone for sustained periods of time, which is not to say that one must live alone, obsessively.
author: Joyce Carol Oates

quote_original: I'm fiercely independent, but I'm also terrified of being alone.
author: Adam Levine

quote_original: As a child, I had to get up early for school or work. I'd get ready by myself. I'd set my alarm to wake me up very early in the morning, and be off to work, the family driver driving me every morning. I did it alone, my parents never coming in to wake me up.
author: Janet Jackson

quote_original: It is eerie being all but alone in Westminster Abbey. Without the tourists, there are only the dead, many of them kings and queens. They speak powerfully and put my thoughts into vivid perspective.
author: A. N. Wilson

quote_original: Life is only a long and bitter suicide, and faith alone can transform this suicide into a sacrifice.
author: Franz Liszt

quote_original: For so long as the Jew has even one ally, he will be convinced - in his smallness of mind - that his salvation came from that ally. It is only when he is alone - against all of his own efforts and frantic attempts - that he will, through no choice, be compelled to turn to G-d.
author: Meir Kahane

quote_original: But it seems that the judging maybe they shouldn't at least see the practices all week long. That can taint the way they go into the judging and the outlook of what's going to happen, instead of just watching those four minutes and judging on those minutes alone.
author: Nancy Kerrigan

quote_original: No one chooses to raise children alone.
author: Erykah Badu

quote_original: I'm not saying that there's anything better than mated bliss at its best, but I'm saying that living alone is as good in its own way. But we haven't quite given ourselves permission to recognize that.
author: Barbara Feldon

quote_original: It was either Voltaire or Charlie Sheen who said, 'We are born alone. We live alone. We die alone. And anything in between that can give us the illusion that we're not, we cling to.'
author: Gabriel Byrne

quote_original: Most bands don't even last fourteen months let alone fourteen years.
author: Peter Steele

quote_original: I was very happy sitting alone at a dining room table, writing a script.
author: Conrad Hall

quote_original: It's always easier if you have the support of your family, if you're not alone. I came from a country that has been through a lot of troubles in the last 20 to 30 years, but we have been through them together.
author: Novak Djokovic

quote_original: It's an amazing feeling to go into a studio and really be alone.
author: Joaquin Phoenix

quote_original: Not drunk is he who from the floor - Can rise alone and still drink more But drunk is They, who prostrate lies, Without the power to drink or rise.
author: Thomas Love Peacock

quote_original: Whatever my individual desires were to be free, I was not alone. There were many others who felt the same way.
author: Rosa Parks

quote_original: I'm never less at leisure than when at leisure, or less alone than when alone.
author: Scipio Africanus

quote_original: I'm ultimately a widow and a single mother, who's not even getting to be a mother right now. I am so alone, it's freaky.
author: Courtney Love

quote_original: I have my best ideas when I am alone.
author: Leona Lewis

quote_original: I learned why 'out riding alone' is an oxymoron: An equestrian is never alone, is always sensing the other being, the mysterious but also understandable living being that is the horse.
author: Jane Smiley

quote_original: When I walked to school in the mornings I would start out alone but would pick up four other boys along the way. We would set out together after school across the village green.
author: Roald Dahl

quote_original: You can't get rid of it with exercise alone. You can do the most vigorous exercise and only burn up 300 calories in an hour. If you've got fat on your body, the exercise firms and tones the muscles. But when you use that tape measure, what makes it bigger? It's the fat!
author: Jack LaLanne

quote_original: I'm not into watching stuff I did last week, let alone three or four years ago.
author: Chris Hemsworth

quote_original: The accumulation of skill and science which has been directed to diminish the difficulty of producing manufactured goods, has not been beneficial to that country alone in which it is concentrated distant kingdoms have participated in its advantages.
author: Charles Babbage

quote_original: Photography can never grow up if it imitates some other medium. It has to walk alone it has to be itself.
author: Berenice Abbott

quote_original: Postmodernism surely requires an even greater grasp of symbolism, as it's increasingly an art of gesture alone.
author: Andrew Eldritch

quote_original: I try to push ideas away, and the ones that will not leave me alone are the ones that ultimately end up happening.
author: J. J. Abrams

quote_original: Writing is a solitary occupation. Family, friends, and society are the natural enemies of the writer. He must be alone, uninterrupted, and slightly savage if he is to sustain and complete an undertaking.
author: Jessamyn West

quote_original: I'm a workaholic. Before long I'm traveling on my nervous energy alone. This is incredibly exhausting.
author: Eva Gabor

quote_original: I had to weave and play around with a honey bear, you know, and I could wrestle with him a little bit, but there's no way you can even wrestle a honey bear, let alone a grizzly bear that's standing ten feet to eleven feet tall! Can you imagine? But it was fascinating to work that close to that kind of animal.
author: Leslie Nielsen

quote_original: Women are smart in business and dumb in love. They won't date outside their zip code, let alone outside the city. They are city snobs.
author: Patti Stanger

quote_original: However, anyone to whom this happens should not leave his room upon awakening, should speak to no-one, but remain alone and sober until everything comes back to him, and he recalls the dream.
author: Paracelsus

quote_original: The question is what will Mitt Romney do as president if his policy is simply to be hands off and let the government be made so small it can be drowned in a bathtub. In the 21st century global economy, no state alone has the ability to compete against China.
author: Jennifer Granholm

quote_original: I was a little doubtful about the propriety of going to the Mammoth Cave without a gentleman escort, but if two ladies travel alone they must have the courage of men.
author: Maria Mitchell

quote_original: You can work on the saxophone alone, but ultimately you must perform with others.
author: Steve Lacy

quote_original: I'm really lucky that my record companies have been patient with me and leave me alone and give me the time to make it right in my mind.
author: Sarah McLachlan

quote_original: I think sometimes all you need is to hear someone else say the same thing that you're going through to realize that you're not alone. I try to put some sense of hope into the songs, into whatever the situation is so that it's not just dirt, drudgery and a life of misery.
author: Sarah McLachlan

quote_original: It's only when you're alone that you realize where you are. You have nothing to fall back on except your own resources.
author: Paul Theroux

quote_original: The best part about being with a group is that you don't have to do everything alone. You're with your friends.
author: Justin Timberlake

quote_original: In a civilized society, all crimes are likely to be sins, but most sins are not and ought not to be treated as crimes. Man's ultimate responsibility is to God alone.
author: Geoffrey Fisher

quote_original: People love pretty much the same things best. A writer looking for subjects inquires not after what he loves best, but after what he alone loves at all.
author: Annie Dillard

quote_original: Buddhism notes that it is always a mistake to think your soul can go it alone.
author: Annie Dillard

quote_original: Good acting is all in the writing. If it isn't on the page, then it really won't make any difference. You cannot act on force of personality alone.
author: Larry Hagman

quote_original: I just broke up with my boyfriend, and I've been spending more time alone than I'd like.
author: Lucinda Williams

quote_original: I live to hail that season by gifted one foretold, when men shall live by reason, and not alone by gold.
author: George Linnaeus Banks

quote_original: Man cannot live by incompetence alone.
author: Charlotte Whitton

quote_original: The power of a book lies in its power to turn a solitary act into a shared vision. As long as we have books, we are not alone.
author: Laura Bush

quote_original: I know that books I have written will still resonate in 50 years - particularly 'My Sister's Keeper.' It has sold three million copies in the States alone. I strongly feel that, as a novelist, you have a platform and the ability to change people's minds.
author: Jodi Picoult

quote_original: With fame there is a crosswire between intensity and intimacy. You have decoy intimacy, but you are also very much alone.
author: Mike Myers

quote_original: Do not rely completely on any other human being, however dear. We meet all life's greatest tests alone.
author: Agnes Macphail

quote_original: In the country of pain we are each alone.
author: May Sarton

quote_original: People like eccentrics. Therefore they will leave me alone, saying that I am a mad clown.
author: Vaslav Nijinsky

quote_original: If you would have your son to walk honourably through the world, you must not attempt to clear the stones from his path, but teach him to walk firmly over them - not insist upon leading him by the hand, but let him learn to go alone.
author: Anne Bronte

quote_original: All still lifes are actually paintings of the world on the sixth day of creation, when God and the world were alone together, without man!
author: Robert Musil

quote_original: I'm a huge Wes Anderson fan I would faint if I met him, let alone got to work with him.
author: Emma Roberts

quote_original: Forbidden pleasures alone are loved immoderately when lawful, they do not excite desire.
author: Quintilian

quote_original: As regards parents, I should like to see them as highly educated as possible, and I do not restrict this remark to fathers alone.
author: Quintilian

quote_original: Government alone cannot solve the problems we deal with in our correctional facilities, treatment centers, homeless shelters and crisis centers - we need our faith-based and community partners.
author: Dirk Kempthorne

quote_original: Whoever wants to know something about me - as an artist which alone is significant - they should look attentively at my pictures and there seek to recognise what I am and what I want.
author: Gustav Klimt

quote_original: Let your mind alone, and see what happens.
author: Virgil Thomson

quote_original: I rise to taste the dawn, and find that love alone will shine today.
author: Ken Wilber

quote_original: If men knew how women pass the time when they are alone, they'd never marry.
author: O. Henry

quote_original: Americans different in some maybe thoughts or emphasis still have the same ideas. They want a government that lets them be free, that leaves them alone, that doesn't interrupt and interfere with every aspect of their life, that lets them go to work and keep more of what they've worked hard to have.
author: Mike Huckabee

quote_original: A good government may, indeed, redress the grievances of an injured people but a strong people can alone build up a great nation.
author: Thomas Francis Meagher

quote_original: I made some friends at Listerine and they taught me a little bit about oral care. That half of adults suffer from oral disease, that the number one chronic disease among children is oral disease, that we're only taking care of 25% of our mouths when brushing alone and there are more germs in your mouth than there are people on the planet.
author: Ginnifer Goodwin

quote_original: I would point out that I'm an actress for a reason! If I were popular in high school, I would have considered another career because I wouldn't have been alone in my room, making up other characters for myself. I definitely had growing pains. The popular kids didn't want anything to do with the girl who was starting the drama club.
author: Ginnifer Goodwin

quote_original: Some players you pat their butts, some players you kick their butts, some players you leave alone.
author: Pete Rose

quote_original: My overcoat is worn out my shirts also are worn out. And I ask to be allowed to have a lamp in the evening it is indeed wearisome sitting alone in the dark.
author: William Tyndale

quote_original: As for style, there is something about the way musicians dress-they seem to be able to create their own world within their fashion alone.
author: Nicole Richie

quote_original: One definition of eternity is that we are not alone on this planet, that there are those who've gone before and those who will come, and that there is a community of spirits.
author: Rita Dove

quote_original: I think Mr. Wilson will have to be the rest of the way alone.
author: Flip Wilson

quote_original: In art, all who have done something other than their predecessors have merited the epithet of revolutionary and it is they alone who are masters.
author: Paul Gauguin

quote_original: In truth, I am a single mother. But I don't feel alone at all in parenting my daughter. Krishna has a whole other side of her family who loves her, too. And so Krishna is parented by me, but also by her grandmother and aunts and cousins and uncles and friends.
author: Padma Lakshmi

quote_original: No one can arrive from being talented alone, work transforms talent into genius.
author: Anna Pavlova

quote_original: In the U.S. alone, weather disasters caused $50 billion in economic damages in 2010.
author: Jeff Goodell

quote_original: Style used to be an interaction between the human soul and tools that were limiting. In the digital era, it will have to come from the soul alone.
author: Jaron Lanier

quote_original: What does it mean to not be alone? I've approached that question through music, technology, writing and other means.
author: Jaron Lanier

quote_original: I understand and get when kids and teenagers feel like they're alone and it's not going to get better. My advice is that there is a support system out there, there are a lot of people who have been through what you're going through and are going through it now.
author: Brittany Snow

quote_original: No enterprise, small or large, public or private, can remain self-governing, let alone successful, so deeply in hock to others as we are about to be.
author: Mitch Daniels

quote_original: The methods by which a trade union can alone act, are necessarily destructive its organization is necessarily tyrannical.
author: Henry George

quote_original: Our country will, I believe, sooner forgive an officer for attacking an enemy than for letting it alone.
author: Horatio Nelson

quote_original: To share our stories is not only a worthwhile endeavor for the storyteller, but for those who hear our stories and feel less alone because of it.
author: Joyce Maynard

quote_original: The English Bible - a book which, if everything else in our language should perish, would alone suffice to show the whole extent of its beauty and power.
author: Thomas B. Macaulay

quote_original: The object of oratory alone in not truth, but persuasion.
author: Thomas B. Macaulay

quote_original: The best rules to form a young man, are, to talk little, to hear much, to reflect alone upon what has passed in company, to distrust one's own opinions, and value others that deserve it.
author: William Temple

quote_original: Science is analytical, descriptive, informative. Man does not live by bread alone, but by science he attempts to do so. Hence the deadliness of all that is purely scientific.
author: Eric Gill

quote_original: 'Tis the last rose of summer Left blooming alone All her lovely companions Are faded and gone.
author: Thomas More

quote_original: Lord, Bless our enemies have mercy upon them, may they turn their course and let us alone, and let us live in peace at our homes in our own native land.
author: William Pennington

quote_original: I grew up in a very large family in a very small house. I never slept alone until after I was married.
author: Lewis Grizzard

quote_original: I like singer-songwriters, and I find sad songs comforting rather than depressing. It makes you realise you're not alone in the world.
author: Natalie Imbruglia

quote_original: Without strength and courage it's really hard to perform at the highest levels of international figure skating, because you're alone on the ice and you only have seven minutes over two nights to prove yourself.
author: Scott Hamilton

quote_original: Life is so impermanent that it's not about somebody else or things around me, it's about knowing you are completely alone in this world and being content inside.
author: K. D. Lang

quote_original: Woman must have her freedom, the fundamental freedom of choosing whether or not she will be a mother and how many children she will have. Regardless of what man's attitude may be, that problem is hers - and before it can be his, it is hers alone.
author: Margaret Sanger

quote_original: The foundations of a strong economy don't rest alone on the decisions of Chancellors or the spending programmes of government.
author: George Osborne

quote_original: You can't play a symphony alone, it takes an orchestra to play it.
author: Navjot Singh Sidhu

quote_original: For the first time, I lived alone... in a luxury apartment on Sunset Strip. For a few days I loved the idea, but I got lonely and restless.
author: Patty Duke

quote_original: People must insist on the right to say no, to be alone, to stand out from the herd. Creative artists can say all this in their own way and in their own field, by hard, rigorous work.
author: Tahar Ben Jelloun

quote_original: The right to be let alone is the underlying principle of the Constitution's Bill of Rights.
author: Erwin Griswold

quote_original: In days of doubt, in days of dreary musings on my country's fate, you alone are my comfort and support, oh great, powerful, righteous, and free Russian language!
author: Ivan Turgenev

quote_original: At the moment of childbirth, every woman has the same aura of isolation, as though she were abandoned, alone.
author: Boris Pasternak

quote_original: Of all our possessions, wisdom alone is imortal.
author: Isocrates

quote_original: What good is sitting all alone in your room?
author: Liza Minnelli

quote_original: A career is all very well, but no one lives by work alone.
author: Lorna Luft

quote_original: Happiness must be cultivated. It is like character. It is not a thing to be safely let alone for a moment, or it will run to weeds.
author: Elizabeth Stuart Phelps

quote_original: The biggest opportunity in 2013 is in Africa. It has seven out of the ten fastest-growing economies in the world. In Nigeria alone there are 100 million people with mobile phones. In total, 300 million Africans - five times the population of Britain - are in the middle class.
author: David Miliband

quote_original: The problems that the world faces - from nuclear proliferation to climate change - can't be tackled by the West alone. They need a coalition of not just West and East, but they need a coalition of Christian and Jew and Muslim.
author: David Miliband

quote_original: This is nourishing, redemptive we become less alone inside.
author: David Foster Wallace

quote_original: I would say, 'I'm alone, but I'm not lonely.' But I was just kidding myself.
author: Bruce Willis

quote_original: He who does not fill his world with phantoms remains alone.
author: Antonio Porchia

quote_original: I used to do a lot of interviews in the early '80s, when my career started, but it came to a point when I decided I didn't want to talk anymore, and people kind of understood that and left me alone.
author: George Strait

quote_original: So many people suffer from abuse, and suffer alone.
author: Pamela Stephenson

quote_original: Men was formed for society, and is neither capable of living alone, nor has the courage to do it.
author: William Blackstone

quote_original: Is it not careless to become too local when there are four hundred billion stars in our galaxy alone.
author: A. R. Ammons

quote_original: You can either invade a country or leave them alone and trade with them. When goods cross borders, armies don't.
author: John Stossel

quote_original: It's a terrible thing to be alone - yes it is - it is - but don't lower your mask until you have another mask prepared beneath - as terrible as you like - but a mask.
author: Katherine Mansfield

quote_original: You'd think I'd have been happiest in my life playing music in front of 50,000 people at Gillette Stadium. But let me tell you, it's an odd feeling to feel alone in the spotlight.
author: Kenny Chesney

quote_original: You're alone in your ideas, because you're the only one who knows what's possible.
author: Bethenny Frankel

quote_original: I was born to be alone, and I always shall be but now I want to be.
author: Mary MacLane

quote_original: I've performed solo for 20 years now, but I don't do much of it, because if you only play alone, you go crazy and out of tune and play foolish music.
author: Steve Lacy

quote_original: Nobody was playing the soprano saxophone and certainly nobody was trying to do anything with it. So I was all alone. I didn't know that at first.
author: Steve Lacy

quote_original: We're all outsiders in a way. We're all alone and can become very lonely.
author: Hugo Weaving

quote_original: I delight in my family obligations, but they leave little time for breaks let alone quick trips across the country.
author: Carre Otis

quote_original: The employee is regarded by the employer merely in the light of his value as an operative. His productive capacity alone is taken into account.
author: Leland Stanford

quote_original: I feel less alone when I read the books of Ratzinger.
author: Oriana Fallaci

quote_original: You know golf is very lonely. When I'm in the States, I feel like if I just think about Taiwan, my friends, my fans, I won't feel like I'm alone.
author: Yani Tseng

quote_original: Even crushed against his brother in the Tube the average Englishman pretends desperately that he is alone.
author: Germaine Greer

quote_original: We've just got to be careful - with all sports, let alone cricket - I think there's so much emphasis on doing the right thing all the time, but I think the public want to be entertained when they come to watch sport.
author: Shane Warne

quote_original: It depends on the situation. I mean, on one hand there's the argument that people should be left alone on the other hand, there's the argument to wade in a stop slaughters in places like Bosnia and Kosovo and what we probably should have done in Rwanda.
author: Jello Biafra

quote_original: Picture yourself vividly as winning, and that alone will contribute immeasurably to success.
author: Harry Emerson Fosdick

quote_original: When I was in my early 20s, I had my hair permed. Bad idea! It turned into total frizz. My advice to women is, if you have nice hair already, don't get a perm, leave your hair alone!
author: Mariska Hargitay

quote_original: The development of beauty in chess never depends on you alone. No matter how much imagination and creativity you invest, you still do not create beauty. Your opponent must react at the same highest level.
author: Vladimir Kramnik

quote_original: I don't know that I spent any more time alone than any other kid, but being by myself never bothered me.
author: Joseph Barbera

quote_original: I still don't like going to bed alone.
author: James Franco

quote_original: Improvisation is almost like the retarded cousin in the comedy world. We've been trying forever to get improvisation on TV. It's just like stand-up. It's best when it's just left alone. It doesn't translate always on TV. It's best live.
author: Amy Poehler

quote_original: Look, the center right coalition in American politics today is best understood as a coalition of groups and individuals that on the issue that brings them to politics what they want from the government is to be left alone.
author: Grover Norquist

quote_original: Luckily, my husband is my business partner as well as my life partner, so I never had to do the heavy lifting alone, literally or figuratively.
author: Josie Maran

quote_original: Religion is the possibility of the removal of every ground of confidence except confidence in God alone.
author: Karl Barth

quote_original: Smart businesses do not look at labor costs alone anymore. They do look at market access, transportation, telecommunications infrastructure and the education and skill level of the workforce, the development of capital and the regulatory market.
author: Janet Napolitano

quote_original: Your Majesty, I took the liberty because I was so desirous of visiting alone with you for a few minutes before the rest of the other peasants arrived.
author: Walter Annenberg

quote_original: If you talk to geneticists they are constantly finding that your genes are being switched on and off because of the environment. Genes alone do not determine an exact path in your life.
author: Jeffrey Eugenides

quote_original: Yes, I am seeking a husband. As soon as the right man asks me, I shall say, It is not good for a woman to live alone.
author: Anna Held

quote_original: I knew I was alone in a way that no earthling has ever been before.
author: Michael Collins

quote_original: Other nations use 'force' we Britons alone use 'Might'.
author: Evelyn Waugh

quote_original: With 'Twilight,' you have these massive tomes that you have to condense. With 'Penoza,' we had an eight episode Dutch series that, just for the pilot alone, I condensed three episodes. So, there's a lot of filling in and a ton of invention that has to happen to fill out eight episodes.
author: Melissa Rosenberg

quote_original: Is there no Latin word for Tea? Upon my soul, if I had known that I would have let the vulgar stuff alone.
author: Hilaire Belloc

quote_original: For me the Anita series is built like a mystery series, which means that as much as possible each book stands alone, so you have a mystery to solve from the beginning to the end of the book.
author: Laurell K. Hamilton

quote_original: It helps to be able to be alone. 'Cuz writing is done alone, unless you collaborate, but I don't do that. Ask my ex-wife.
author: Dirk Benedict

quote_original: My favorite thing is to be alone in a room with a blank paper in front of me and the time to fill it.
author: Dirk Benedict

quote_original: The question of whether or to what extent human activities are causing global warming is not a matter of ideology, let alone of belief. The issue is simply one of risk management.
author: Malcolm Turnbull

quote_original: Once you grow past Mommy and Daddy coming running when you're hurt, you're really on your own. You're alone, and there's no one to help you.
author: Octavia Butler

quote_original: The only people who like to live alone more than comics are priests.
author: Colin Quinn

quote_original: I feel most empires fell when they started to act human, but then look at Russia. They kept a pretty strong hand, and they fell from Afghanistan alone because Afghanistan is the graveyard of empires. I guess you just can't sustain it.
author: Colin Quinn

quote_original: I like my life alone.
author: Sarah Silverman

quote_original: By 2050, the Australian population is expected to grow from 22 million to 36 million. That increase alone will put huge pressure on our towns and our cities. We will need more homes, more roads, more rail lines, more hospitals, more schools, just to accommodate so many Australians.
author: Kevin Rudd

quote_original: Very few people are original. There's very little original anything out there. Because to be original means you have to stand alone.
author: Susan Powter

quote_original: Californians invented the concept of life-style. This alone warrants their doom.
author: Don DeLillo

quote_original: He travels fastest who travels alone, and that goes double for she. Real feminism is spinsterhood.
author: Florence King

quote_original: The Lord had the wonderful advantage of being able to work alone.
author: Kofi Annan

quote_original: Your life is yours and yours alone. Rise up and live it.
author: Terry Goodkind

quote_original: By far the greatest part of those goods which are the objects of desire, are procured by labour and they may be multiplied, not in one country alone, but in many, almost without any assignable limit, if we are disposed to bestow the labour necessary to obtain them.
author: David Ricardo

quote_original: Trust him not with your secrets, who, when left alone in your room, turns over your papers.
author: Johann Kaspar Lavater

quote_original: You may tell a man thou art a fiend, but not your nose wants blowing to him alone who can bear a thing of that kind, you may tell all.
author: Johann Kaspar Lavater

quote_original: Between 1910 and 1950 approximately 350 lives of Jesus were published in the English language alone.
author: John Clayton

quote_original: You watch a hockey game, and the hand-eye coordination and the speed is really miraculous how those guys track the puck alone, just following it with their eyes.
author: Liev Schreiber

quote_original: I never wanted to go on stage alone because if you mess up, who can you blame?
author: Patti LaBelle

quote_original: I don't know much about only children. I was the middle one of three, and if ever I was alone with mum and dad, it was a rare moment.
author: Elizabeth Hurley

quote_original: Now, on nights that I can't sleep, I play video games alone until the morning.
author: Namie Amuro

quote_original: Why can't everybody leave everybody else the hell alone.
author: Jimmy Durante

quote_original: I don't wanna hear nobody complain that they're getting paid all this money and people won't leave them alone. It's part of it.
author: Mark Wahlberg

quote_original: It's very hard to write a song alone. It's only by jamming that you can get a song together.
author: Maurice Gibb

quote_original: I was able to support myself by acting alone about six years ago. Until then, I was just scraping by.
author: Edie Falco

quote_original: Eagles commonly fly alone. They are crows, daws, and starlings that flock together.
author: John Webster

quote_original: I like being alone and I think this movie, as much as it is an investigation of connection and people bonding, I also think it's just as much about loneliness.
author: Jason Schwartzman

quote_original: I am very averse to bringing myself forward in print, but as my account will only appear as an appendage to a former production, and as it will be confined to such topics as have connection with my authorship alone, I can hardly accuse myself of a personal intrusion.
author: Mary Wollstonecraft Shelley

quote_original: The secret to being a writer is that you have to write. It's not enough to think about writing or to study literature or plan a future life as an author. You really have to lock yourself away, alone, and get to work.
author: Augusten Burroughs

quote_original: When I was old enough to go to movies alone, I got to see 'Frankenstein' and 'Dracula' on the big screen. I just fell in love with them.
author: George A. Romero

quote_original: Autobiography begins with a sense of being alone. It is an orphan form.
author: John Berger

quote_original: Young people discovering their sexuality must know they walk with a strong tradition and that they are not alone. They have a right to information without being pressured.
author: Jasmine Guy

quote_original: Laws are generally found to be nets of such a texture, as the little creep through, the great break through, and the middle-sized are alone entangled in it.
author: William Shenstone

quote_original: The athlete of today is not an athlete alone. He's the center of a team - doctors, scientists, coaches, agents and so on.
author: Emil Zatopek

quote_original: I don't treat the band like I'm above them or that they're a hired hand for me. We've never worked that way. So I'm a team player. I would be very uncomfortable having to do this alone.
author: Tom Petty

quote_original: It is said that man doesn't live by bread alone. Sometimes this is unfortunate, because people who cannot live by bread alone too often kill other people in consequence of the fights they get into.
author: John McCarthy

quote_original: For an adult, eating alone at McDonald's is admitting a kind of defeat.
author: Jonathan Carroll

quote_original: I tour alone. There's no sound check, no back up. I stay with the hosts I am in a family home and it's really nourishing. I just have to remember after the show not to run out into the living room in my pyjamas. Every day, it's a new relationship being built. It's odd and wonderful.
author: Jane Siberry

quote_original: I hope this will help new moms not feel alone or desperate, and that there is no shame in their feelings. PPD is out of their control, but the treatment and healing process is not.
author: Brooke Shields

quote_original: It's good that the first half of the speech emphasized freedom, because George W. Bush has been the global champion for freedom. As he said, if we don't fight tyranny it will not leave us alone in peace.
author: Ernest Istook

quote_original: All my fans tell me what a glamorous life I have, but I tell them how hard I work and how many nights I spend alone with my dogs, eating chicken pot pie in my bedroom.
author: Shannen Doherty

quote_original: I've been left alone, even by the paparazzi, because what sells is sex and scandal. Absent that, they really don't have much interest in you. I'm still married, still working, still happy.
author: Matt Damon

quote_original: Although born in a prosperous realm, we did not believe that its boundaries should limit our knowledge, and that the lore of the East should alone enlighten us.
author: Charles de Secondat

quote_original: Science and vision are not opposites or even at odds. They need each other. I sometimes hear other startup folks say something along the lines of: 'If entrepreneurship was a science, then anyone could do it.' I'd like to point out that even science is a science, and still very few people can do it, let alone do it well.
author: Eric Ries

quote_original: A movie like House of the Dead with around $7 million budget or Alone in the Dark with around $16 million budget are much easier to make profit than the typical $50 million major motion picture.
author: Uwe Boll

quote_original: If you're truly in a band and you guys have been together for a long time, there's a family bond that you have. In fact, I've talked about this with therapists, especially if you're talking about a relationship, because when you're with somebody, you're going to your family, and she's alone.
author: Gary Allan

quote_original: I mean one of the things about being alone is that you've no people to define yourself off, I mean, people are like all-round mirrors, because let's face it, we don't often see ourselves all round in a mirror anyway, do we.
author: Diana Wynne Jones

quote_original: The devil had as good have let Paul alone, for he no sooner comes into prison but he falls a preaching, at which the gates of Satan's prison fly open, and poor sinners come forth.
author: William Gurnall

quote_original: Every three days on average, I am alone on stage, facing the public.
author: Placido Domingo

quote_original: But in the end, in the end one is alone. We are all of us alone. I mean I'm told these days we have to consider ourselves as being in society... but in the end one knows one is alone, that one lives at the heart of a solitude.
author: Harold Bloom

quote_original: The Jew does not wish to be isolated. He fears being alone, without allies.
author: Meir Kahane

quote_original: I think that in itself is kind of an amazing achievement to be able to say that your full-time career is in any creative arts, let alone a show that has kept people interested for coming on four seasons and hopefully more.
author: Anna Paquin

quote_original: In today's interdependent world, a threat to one becomes a menace to all. And no state can defeat these challenges and threats alone.
author: Michelle Bachelet

quote_original: Artists walk alone.
author: Ezra Miller

quote_original: Christmas lights may be the loneliest thing for me, especially if you mix them up with reindeers and sleighs. I feel alone. I feel isolated. I feel I do not belong.
author: Mira Nair

quote_original: In my cranky old age, I actually prefer recording alone now, on 'The Simpsons,' for example, because I find that the director can just focus on what I'm doing and I can do a lot of variations. A lot of times, when I record with a group, I'll stay after class for another hour or two.
author: Hank Azaria

quote_original: I'm so secluded. Very alone.
author: Yves Saint Laurent

quote_original: It felt like the first thing, but when I first started out, I got a job adapting a book by Russell Banks called 'Rule Of The Bone.' I didn't do a very good job. I didn't really know what I was doing in general, let alone how to adapt a book.
author: Paul Thomas Anderson

quote_original: Let me alone: I have yet my legs and one arm. Tell the surgeon to make haste and his instruments. I know I must lose my right arm, so the sooner it's off the better.
author: Horatio Nelson

quote_original: On the stage, you alone hold the key, and on the night you have to trust that the director has inspired you enough to take the material and run with it.
author: Greta Scacchi

quote_original: We cannot know the whole truth, which belongs to God alone, but our task nevertheless is to seek to know what is true. And if we offend gravely enough against what we know to be true, as by failing badly enough to deal affectionately and responsibly with our land and our neighbors, truth will retaliate with ugliness, poverty, and disease.
author: Wendell Berry

quote_original: I am convinced that living in an enclave shapes the personality, and living alone shapes the personality too.
author: Mary Douglas

quote_original: European investment in Texas alone exceeds all U.S. investment in China and Japan put together.
author: John Bruton

quote_original: There's great sadness and life doesn't work out like you would want, on a lot of levels, but there's no need to feel all alone. This happens to everybody, so there's no self-pity. This is the ride that humans are on, and all of it is essential for our natural part of it.
author: Mike Mills

quote_original: I am aware that in presenting myself as the advocate of the Indians and their rights, I shall stand very much alone.
author: Sam Houston

quote_original: A singer for me is more like someone who is standing alone with a microphone like Scott Walker, rather than someone who is bashing a plank and is spitting all over a microphone.
author: Graham Coxon

quote_original: You have to respect your audience. Without them, you're essentially standing alone, singing to yourself.
author: K. D. Lang

quote_original: She goes through the vale of death alone, each time a babe is born. As it is the right neither of man nor the state to coerce her into this ordeal, so it is her right to decide whether she will endure it.
author: Margaret Sanger

quote_original: There's nobody else on the face of this earth that's playing a sport at a highest level... with a transplant. That alone continues to inspire me, because I realize throughout the whole world the struggles that people are going through. I need to inspire them the best way I can.
author: Alonzo Mourning

quote_original: This communication alone, by the comparison of the antagonisms, rivalries, movements which give birth to decisive moments, permits the evolution of the soul, whereby a man realizes himself on earth. It is impossible to be concerned with anything else in art.
author: Robert Delaunay

quote_original: I think all teenagers feel alone, and that nobody else knows what they are going through and all that sort of stuff.
author: Nicholas Hoult

quote_original: Life certainly points it out to you - 'you can go this way or the other way.' You have to decide and it's a very strong decision because, would you sleep well knowing that you're living in the best place, but you're letting the place where you should live alone?
author: Gael Garcia Bernal

quote_original: People with fertility problems are not alone. It is a very very common problem for couples today. I've seen statistics that are just staggering.
author: Michael Zaslow

quote_original: No One Is Alone by Stephen Sondheim is all about thinking for yourself and being your own person.
author: Bernadette Peters

quote_original: I sailboat raced, I love to go out on my motorcycle alone, but I also love my family dearly. I love that aspect of my life as well.
author: Bob Seger

quote_original: Shockingly, a University of Pennsylvania study says the number of young people addicted to gambling - largely due to increased exposure to the Internet and Internet gambling - grew by an alarming 20 percent between 2004 and 2005 alone.
author: Spencer Bachus

quote_original: My early childhood prepared me to be a social psychologist. I grew up in a South Bronx ghetto in a very poor family. From Sicilian origin, I was the first person in my family to complete high school, let alone go to college.
author: Philip Zimbardo

quote_original: Anyone who writes knows that ultimately the majority of your time is spent alone in a room with a piano or a guitar, no matter what the project is.
author: Trey Anastasio

quote_original: You have to understand the tone of the movie, because if it's supposed to be funny, it can be funny violent like the Home Alone stuff, but you have to really understand the tone of what you're doing and make the action work for that and for the character.
author: David R. Ellis

quote_original: As the only girl growing up among three brothers, I was always afraid of being excluded. If there was a game to be played, a sport to be learned, a competition to join, I was on my feet and ready. I didn't spend much time alone for fear that I'd miss out.
author: Elisabeth Shue

quote_original: I like to read books and be alone I'm not social butterfly person.
author: Hope Solo

quote_original: I don't know. I think it's funny! I think it's funny! I go, what? It's so absurd. I'm alone.
author: Danny DeVito

quote_original: I personally love to run outdoor fitness trails. I love the meditative value I get when out alone, challenging myself to run faster and higher.
author: Laurieann Gibson

quote_original: I can work myself up into a fearful, paralyzing state of mind that can last for days, weeks even months where I feel mad, totally isolated and alone, overwhelmed and completely out of control.
author: Vinny Guadagnino

quote_original: I can't write without a reader. It's precisely like a kiss - you can't do it alone.
author: John Cheever

quote_original: Glasgow's not a media center. When you're there, when you're hanging about, you feel quite detached from musical movements or fashions or anything like that. You do feel quite alone, in a good way.
author: Alex Kapranos

quote_original: I believe in capitalism for everybody, not necessarily high finance but capitalism that works for the working men and women of this country who are out there paddling alone in America right now.
author: Rick Santorum

quote_original: But there's not enough time in life to go sit at a party, have a drink, and make idle conversation. There's too many important things to do. Just being together with my husband, spending time alone, which I have very little of.
author: Pia Zadora

quote_original: Tell me who is able to keep his bed chaste, or which goddess is able to live with one god alone?
author: Sextus Propertius

quote_original: A book is sent out into the world, and there is no way of fully anticipating the responses it will elicit. Consider the responses called forth by the Bible, Homer, Shakespeare - let alone contemporary poetry or a modern novel.
author: Chaim Potok

quote_original: I feel completely alone - it's like melting, I am the structure, and I am also Alain Robert.
author: Alain Robert
